BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4853@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020723Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION: \n\nOff Night Productions presents Hurricane Diane by Madelein
 e George\, on stage August 3-12 at the Waldron Auditorium in downtown Bloo
 mington.\n\nIn Hurricane Diane\, the Greek god Dionysus returns to the mod
 ern world— disguised as the butch gardener Diane—whose secret mission is t
 o seduce mortal fol\nlowers and restore the earth to its natural state. Wh
 ere better to begin than with four real housewives from New Jersey?\nShowt
 imes are: August 3rd & 10th @ 2pm\, August 4th\, 5th\, 11th\, & 12th @7pm
 \n\nTickets on sale through the Buskirk-Chumley Box Office. Meet the cast 
 and learn more at https://offnightproductions.org/hurricanediane25\n\nAbou
 t Off Night Productions\nOff Night Productions (ONP) is a Monroe county-ba
 sed 501(c)3 nonprofit\, women-led theatre company producing contemporary t
 heatre and music on off-nights (Sunday\, Monday\, and Tuesday) of the trad
 itional performance week. Off Night Productions is the only local theater 
 company with the aims of tackling issues and limitations we see in the the
 atre industry locally and globally by extending the traditional performanc
 e week (producing on off-nights)\, prioritizing female and non-binary arti
 stic leadership throughout the creative process\, and practicing sustainab
 ility at every level of production.\nFind tickets and learn more at https:
 //offnightproductions.org/\n\nTickets: https://offnightproductions.org/hur
 ricanediane25.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250803
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20250813
LOCATION:The John & Linda Whikehart Auditorium | Waldron Arts Center @ 122 
 S Walnut St\, Bloomington
