 'aligncenter size-thumbnail wp-image-3929' src='https://writersguildbloomi
 ngton.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/kwong-lisa-2022-150x150.jpg' alt='' w
 idth='150' height='150' /></a></p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>Lisa i
 s a Bloomington writer and poet who teaches at Indiana University and Ivy 
 Tech Community College.</p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>Come hear her
  read from her book <i>Becoming AppalAsian</i> (Glass Lyre Press).</p>\n<p
  style='text-align: center\;'>Her reading will be followed by a conversati
 on about her book\, poetry\, writing\, and anything else that catches her 
 fancy.</p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>The event will take place at M
 orgenstern Books in the back at the conference table.</p>\n<p style='text-
 align: center\;'>The store will have copies of his book for sale prior to 
 and during the event.</p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>Hope to see you
  there!</p>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-3951@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020723Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:NEW BOOK LAUNCH READING\nfeaturing \nHiromi Yoshida\nGuest Read
 er: Tony Brewer\nMC: Joan Hawkins\nOne of Bloomington’s finest and most ou
 tspoken poets\, Hiromi Yoshida is the author of four chapbooks\, the most 
 recent being Icarus Superstar. Her poems have been included in the INverse
  Poetry Archive\, and nominated for the Pushcart Prize\, Best of the Net\,
  the Wilder Poetry Book Prize\, the New Women’s Voices Poetry Prize\, and 
 the Gerald Cable Book Award. She teaches poetry for the Indiana Writers Ce
 nter\, and coordinates the Last Sunday Poetry Reading & Open Mic program f
 or the Writers Guild at Bloomington. She also serves on the board of direc
 tors of the Arts Alliance of Greater Bloomington as a literary arts repres
 entative\, and on the Artistic Advisory Committee of Constellation Stage &
  Screen. While Bloomington has been her delightfully adopted home througho
 ut 27 years of continuous residence\, she can be nostalgic for the New Yor
 k City of the 1970s and 1990s\, featured throughout Icarus Superstar. 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20230322T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20230322T193000
LOCATION:Morgenstern's Bookstore & Cafe @ 849 S. Auto Mall Rd.
SEQUENCE:0
