 rif\;'>MC: Joan Hawkins</span></h3>\n<p class='yiv1537142499MsoNormal' sty
 le='text-align: center\;'><span lang='EN'>One of Bloomington’s finest and 
 most outspoken poets\, </span><span lang='EN'>Hiromi Yoshida is the author
  of four chapbooks\, the most recent being <i>Icarus Superstar</i>. </span
 ><span lang='EN'>Her poems have been included in the INverse Poetry Archiv
 e\, and nominated for the Pushcart Prize\, Best of the Net\, the Wilder Po
 etry Book Prize\, the New Women’s Voices Poetry Prize\, and the Gerald Cab
 le Book Award. She teaches poetry for the Indiana Writers Center\, and coo
