BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-3949@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020723Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:LAST SUNDAY POETRY READING & OPEN MIC\n\nfeaturing\nAngela Jack
 son-Brown and Patsy Rahn\nThe March 2023 edition of Last Sunday Poetry & O
 pen Mic\, sponsored by the Writers Guild @ Bloomington\, celebrates Women’
 s History Month by showcasing Angela Jackson-Brown and Patsy Rahn.\n \nAng
 ela Jackson-Brown is an award-winning writer\, poet\, and playwright. She 
 has published her short fiction\, creative nonfiction\, and poetry in jour
 nals that include The Louisville Journal and Appalachian Review\, and her 
 work has been anthologized in books like Revisiting the Elegy in the Black
  Lives Matter Era\, and Not Like the Rest of Us: An Anthology of Contempor
 ary Indiana Writers. Her scholarly research on co-constructed autoethnogra
 phy\, collaborative teaching\, critical service-learning\, and e-learning 
 has been showcased in publications like the Journal of Black Studies and T
 he Journal of Community Engagement and Higher Education. Her poetry collec
 tion\, House Repairs\, won the Alabama Author Award in Poetry sponsored by
  the Alabama Library Association in 2021.\nwww.angelajacksonbrown.com\n \n
  \nPatsy Rahn‘s poetry and prose have been published in various journals a
 nd anthologies. Her first poetry book\, The Grainy Wet Soul\, was publishe
 d in 2018. In 2021\, she won the People’s Choice Award from the 5th Open E
 urasian Literary Festival of Festivals. She has read for festivals\, liter
 ary events\, private homes\, and pubs\, as well as with the Bloomington Sy
 mphony Orchestra. One public reading on YouTube has received over 1\,500 v
 iews. She continues to give public readings\, and has a second poetry manu
 script in search of a publisher.\nwww.patsyrahn.com\n \n \n \nThe Writers 
 Guild at Bloomington is committed to fostering diversity equity and inclus
 ivity.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20230326T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20230326T163000
LOCATION:Morgenstern's Bookstore & Cafe @ 849 S. Auto Mall Rd.
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Last Sunday Poetry Reading & Open Mic
