BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4018@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020723Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Last Sunday Poetry Reading & Open Mic\n \nSponsored by Indiana 
 Humanities\, and Presented by the Writers Guild at Bloomington\nfeaturing
 \nJL Kato\nWinner of the 2022 Literary Champion Award\nfrom the Eugene and
  Marilyn Glick Indiana Authors Awards\nA Q&A session will be held after th
 e poetry reading instead of open mic.\n \nJL Kato\, Indiana’s 2022 Literar
 y Champion\, will read from his award-winning book\, Shadows Set in Concre
 te.  The reading will be followed by a Q&A session.\nJL Kato was born in J
 apan and moved to Indiana at age two. He graduated from Indiana University
  with a degree in journalism and worked as a newspaper copy editor for 31 
 years.\nHis full-length poetry collection\, Shadows Set in Concrete\, was 
 selected the 2011 Best Indiana Book of Poetry by the Indiana Center for th
 e Book.\nFormer president of Etheridge Knight Inc. and Brick Street Poetry
  — organizations that sponsor literary events\, readings\, contests and pu
 blications — Kato was also a co-founder and curator of Poetry in Free Moti
 on\, a project that combined the creative sparks of quilters and poets.\nA
 s a member of the Indiana Writers Center\, he was a participant\, then mod
 erator\, of the Poetry Salon\, which encouraged poets to develop their wri
 ting and critiquing skills. He also served for six years as poetry editor 
 of Flying Island. Kato volunteers as a judge in the annual writing contest
  for incarcerated persons sponsored by the Woman’s Press Club of Indiana.
 \n 
