 ont-family: Times New Roman\, serif\;'>Eugene and Marilyn Glick Indiana Au
 thors Awards</span></h3>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'><span style='fon
 t-family: Times New Roman\, serif\;'>A Q&A session will be held after the 
 poetry reading instead of open mic.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>JL Ka
 to</strong>\, Indiana’s 2022 Literary Champion\, will read from his award-
 winning book\, Shadows Set in Concrete.  The reading will be followed by a
  Q&A session.</p>\n<p>JL Kato was born in Japan and moved to Indiana at ag
 e two. He graduated from Indiana University with a degree in journalism an
 d worked as a newspaper copy editor for 31 years.</p>\n<p>His full-length 
 poetry collection\, Shadows Set in Concrete\, was selected the 2011 Best I
 ndiana Book of Poetry by the Indiana Center for the Book.</p>\n<p>Former p
 resident of Etheridge Knight Inc. and Brick Street Poetry — organizations 
 that sponsor literary events\, readings\, contests and publications — Kato
  was also a co-founder and curator of Poetry in Free Motion\, a project th
 at combined the creative sparks of quilters and poets.</p>\n<p>As a member
  of the Indiana Writers Center\, he was a participant\, then moderator\, o
 f the Poetry Salon\, which encouraged poets to develop their writing and c
 ritiquing skills. He also served for six years as poetry editor of Flying 
 Island. Kato volunteers as a judge in the annual writing contest for incar
 cerated persons sponsored by the Woman’s Press Club of Indiana.</p>\n<p> <
 /p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'><a href='https://writersguildblooming
