DESCRIPTION:LAST SUNDAY POETRY READING & OPEN MIC\nfeaturing\nC. S. Matthew
 s\, Bree Jo’ann Flannelly\n\n\nPresented by the Writers Guild at Bloomingt
 on\nC. S. MATTHEWS is the author of Redactable\, (The Grind Stone)\, and t
 he forthcoming books\, Phrenology (EMP Press)\, and Ecstatic Birth (Laughi
 ng Ronin Press). Her work has also been published in journals and antholog
 ies. Co-editor of The Grind Stone Press\, she co-hosts the Poetry Speaks r
 eading series in Evansville\, and provides the artwork for front covers of
  the Grind Stone chapbook series.\nBREE JO’ANN FLANNELLY is a multimedia p
 oet pursuing an MFA in Creative Writing from Butler University. She thinks
  a lot about fashion\, the literary space\, video games and neurodiversity
 . Her book Black Glitter was published by Monster House Press in 2018.\n\n
 Emerging poets who need a supportive audience\, and established poets\, wh
 o want to promote published works: Sign up for open mic! Your words are pr
 ecious.\n\nThe Writers Guild at Bloomington is committed to diversity\, eq
 uity\, and inclusivity.
