 ='yiv3584058547MsoNormal' style='text-align: center\;'><span style='font-f
 amily: arial\, sans-serif\;'>C. S. Matthews\, Bree Jo’ann Flannelly</span>
 </h2>\n</div>\n<div style='text-align: center\;'></div>\n<p style='text-al
 ign: center\;'>Presented by the Writers Guild at Bloomington</p>\n<p><stro
 ng>C. S. MATTHEWS</strong> is the author of Redactable\, (The Grind Stone)
 \, and the forthcoming books\, Phrenology (EMP Press)\, and Ecstatic Birth
  (Laughing Ronin Press). Her work has also been published in journals and 
 anthologies. Co-editor of The Grind Stone Press\, she co-hosts the Poetry 
 Speaks reading series in Evansville\, and provides the artwork for front c
 overs of the Grind Stone chapbook series.</p>\n<p><strong>BREE JO’ANN FLAN
 NELL</strong>Y is a multimedia poet pursuing an MFA in Creative Writing fr
 om Butler University. She thinks a lot about fashion\, the literary space\
 , video games and neurodiversity. Her book Black Glitter was published by 
 Monster House Press in 2018.</p>\n<div></div>\n<div style='text-align: cen
 ter\;'>Emerging poets who need a supportive audience\, and established poe
 ts\, who want to promote published works: Sign up for open mic! Your words
  are precious.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div style='text-align: center\;'><em>T
 he Writers Guild at Bloomington is committed to diversity\, equity\, and i
 nclusivity.</em></div>\n<div></div>\n<div style='text-align: center\;'><a 
 href='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/06.23
 -LSP-flyer.jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter si
 ze-medium wp-image-4034' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-conte
 nt/uploads/2023/06/06.23-LSP-flyer-300x232.jpg' alt='' width='300' height=
 '232' /></a></div>\n</BODY></HTML>
