BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4052@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020723Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:First Weds Prose Spoken Word Series\nPresented by the Writers G
 uild at Bloomington\n \nThe featured readers are: Terry Sloan\, with Jon V
 ickers providing\nslides and visuals\; Brian Price\; and music by Jason Fi
 ckel\n\nBackSpace (in Bonne Fête) 112 W 6th St.\n\nCome early to sign up f
 or Open Mic!\n \nGuitarist JASON FICKEL has performed with the VLF Trio\, 
 Jason & Ginger\, and has provided live guitar accompaniment for silent fil
 ms at IU Cinema.\n\nTERRY SLOAN worked at the Indiana University Cyclotron
  Facility for 40 years. He raced motorcycles\, mountain bikes and built an
 d flew an acrobatic biplane. His poems are inspired by movies\, the Beats\
 , general relativity and cosmology. He met Jon Vickers through the IU Cine
 ma and a mutual love of movies. They began to share poems and Jon’s collag
 es. As the collaboration grew\, Jon insisted that this work had to be let 
 loose upon the world and it’s been gaining momentum ever since.\n \nArmed 
 with a degree in civil engineering\, JON VICKERS took his entrepreneurial 
 spirit and love for cinema to open three film venues and programs in the M
 idwest\; Vickers Theatre\, Browning Cinema at the University of Notre Dame
  and Indiana University Cinema. His passion for movies\, poetry and motorc
 ycles forged a fast friendship with Terry Sloan. They believe their creati
 ve work should generate more questions than answers.\n \nBRIAN PRICE is a 
 writer\, director\, and audio producer. He has worked in radio and audio p
 ublishing since the 1980s working with groups such as the Iowa Radio Proje
 ct\, The Grist Mill Horror Series\, Native Voices at the Autry\, and the N
 ational Audio Theatre Festivals. His short comic skits\, plays\, and monol
 ogues have been performed by community groups across the country and two o
 f his plays have been translated into Croatian and Chinese. He is a foundi
 ng partner in Great Northern Audio Theatre\, which created and produced 20
  years of live Mark Time Radio shows for Minnesota’s Convergence Science F
 iction Convention. Their feature-length “In the Embers” received an APA Au
 die Award for Best Audio Drama in 2017. He has published two books of shor
 t fiction\, monologues\, and poetry: “The Old Cart Wrangler\, The New Sile
 nce\, and Other Notions” (2020) and “The Wrong Side of the River and Other
  Points of Interest” (2022). He has some concerns about the general future
  of mankind\, and often gets paid in T-shirts and “gimme hats.” He is a me
 mber in good standing of the “The Electroacoustical Poetical Society.”\n 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20230705T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20230705T200000
