X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><h2 style='text-
 align: center\;'>First Weds Prose Spoken Word Series</h2>\n<p style='text-
 align: center\;'><strong>Presented by the Writers Guild at Bloomington</st
 rong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>The featured readers 
 are:<strong> Terry Sloan\,</strong> with <strong>Jon Vickers</strong> prov
 iding<br />\nslides and visuals\; <strong>Brian Price</strong>\; and music
  by <strong>Jason Fickel</strong></p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>\n<
 p style='text-align: center\;'>BackSpace (in Bonne Fête) 112 W 6th St.</p>
 \n<p style='text-align: center\;'>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>Come e
 arly to sign up for Open Mic!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style='text-align: left\;'
 >Guitarist JASON FICKEL has performed with the VLF Trio\, Jason & Ginger\,
  and has provided live guitar accompaniment for silent films at IU Cinema.
 </p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>\n<p>TERRY SLOAN worked at the India
 na University Cyclotron Facility for 40 years. He raced motorcycles\, moun
 tain bikes and built and flew an acrobatic biplane. His poems are inspired
  by movies\, the Beats\, general relativity and cosmology. He met Jon Vick
 ers through the IU Cinema and a mutual love of movies. They began to share
  poems and Jon’s collages. As the collaboration grew\, Jon insisted that t
 his work had to be let loose upon the world and it’s been gaining momentum
  ever since.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Armed with a degree in civil engineering\, 
 JON VICKERS took his entrepreneurial spirit and love for cinema to open th
 ree film venues and programs in the Midwest\; Vickers Theatre\, Browning C
 inema at the University of Notre Dame and Indiana University Cinema. His p
 assion for movies\, poetry and motorcycles forged a fast friendship with T
 erry Sloan. They believe their creative work should generate more question
 s than answers.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>BRIAN PRICE is a writer\, director\, and
  audio producer. He has worked in radio and audio publishing since the 198
 0s working with groups such as the Iowa Radio Project\, The Grist Mill Hor
 ror Series\, Native Voices at the Autry\, and the National Audio Theatre F
 estivals. His short comic skits\, plays\, and monologues have been perform
 ed by community groups across the country and two of his plays have been t
 ranslated into Croatian and Chinese. He is a founding partner in Great Nor
 thern Audio Theatre\, which created and produced 20 years of live Mark Tim
 e Radio shows for Minnesota’s Convergence Science Fiction Convention. Thei
 r feature-length “In the Embers” received an APA Audie Award for Best Audi
 o Drama in 2017. He has published two books of short fiction\, monologues\
 , and poetry: “The Old Cart Wrangler\, The New Silence\, and Other Notions
 ” (2020) and “The Wrong Side of the River and Other Points of Interest” (2
 022). He has some concerns about the general future of mankind\, and often
  gets paid in T-shirts and “gimme hats.” He is a member in good standing o
 f the “The Electroacoustical Poetical Society.”</p>\n<p> </p>\n</BODY></HT
 ML>
END:VEVENT
