BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4092@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020723Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Last Sunday Poetry Reading & Open Mic\nPresented by The Writers
  Guild at Bloomington\n \nfeaturing Maria Hamilton Abegunde and Bree Jo’an
 n Flannelly\n\nBREE JO’ANN FLANNELLY is a multimedia poet pursuing an MFA 
 in Creative Writing from Butler University. She thinks a lot about fashion
 \, the literary space\, video games and neurodiversity. Her book Black Gli
 tter was published by Monster House Press in 2018.\nMaria Hamilton Abegund
 e is a memory keeper\, ancestral priest\, and full spectrum doula. Her wri
 tings have been published in Obsidian\, Tupelo Quarterly\, the Massachuset
 ts Review\, Black Joy Unbound\, the Kenyon Review\, FIRE!!!\, Trouble the 
 Waters: Tales of the Deep Blue\, ASHE: Ritual Poetics in African Diasporic
  Expression\, and SO WE CAN KNOW: Writers of Color on Pregnancy\, Loss\, A
 bortion\, and Birth. She is the commissioned poet for the Ancestral Masque
 rades\, Keeper of My Mothers’ Dreams\, and Sister Song exhibitions. Dr. Ab
 egunde is a faculty member in African American and African Diaspora Studie
 s at IU. She is a Cave Canem\, Sacatar\, Ragdale\, and Black Earth Institu
 te Fellow.\n\nYou are encouraged to come early to sign up for open mic.
