X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><h2 style='text-
 align: center\;'>Last Sunday Poetry Reading & Open Mic</h2>\n<p style='tex
 t-align: center\;'>Presented by The Writers Guild at Bloomington</p>\n<p> 
 </p>\n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>featuring Maria Hamilton Abegunde a
 nd Bree Jo’ann Flannelly</h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<p><strong>BREE JO’ANN FLANNELLY
 </strong> is a multimedia poet pursuing an MFA in Creative Writing from Bu
 tler University. She thinks a lot about fashion\, the literary space\, vid
 eo games and neurodiversity. Her book Black Glitter was published by Monst
 er House Press in 2018.</p>\n<p><strong>Maria Hamilton Abegunde</strong> i
 s a memory keeper\, ancestral priest\, and full spectrum doula. Her writin
 gs have been published in Obsidian\, Tupelo Quarterly\, the Massachusetts 
 Review\, Black Joy Unbound\, the Kenyon Review\, FIRE!!!\, Trouble the Wat
 ers: Tales of the Deep Blue\, ASHE: Ritual Poetics in African Diasporic Ex
 pression\, and SO WE CAN KNOW: Writers of Color on Pregnancy\, Loss\, Abor
 tion\, and Birth. She is the commissioned poet for the Ancestral Masquerad
 es\, Keeper of My Mothers’ Dreams\, and Sister Song exhibitions. Dr. Abegu
 nde is a faculty member in African American and African Diaspora Studies a
 t IU. She is a Cave Canem\, Sacatar\, Ragdale\, and Black Earth Institute 
 Fellow.</p>\n<div style='text-align: center\;'></div>\n<div style='text-al
 ign: center\;'>You are encouraged to come early to sign up for open mic.</
 div>\n<div></div>\n<div style='text-align: center\;'><a href='https://writ
 ersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/08.23-LSP-flyer-scaled.
 jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter size-medium w
 p-image-4093' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/
 2023/08/08.23-LSP-flyer-300x233.jpg' alt='' width='300' height='233' /></a
 ></div>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
