 ;251\;201\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><div class='ai1e
 c-event-avatar alignleft timely'><img src='https://writersguildbloomington
 .com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/mic-color-lites.jpg' width='251' height='2
 01' /></div><p> </p>\n<h2 style='text-align: center\;'>First Sunday Prose 
 Reading and Open Mic</h2>\n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>Presented by t
 he Writers Guild at Bloomington</h3>\n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>The
  featured readers are<br />\nAntonia Matthew and Shana Ritter</h3>\n<p sty
 le='text-align: center\;'><strong>Come early to sign up for Open Mic!</str
 ong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'><s
 trong>Antonia Matthew</strong> was born in England before World War II. He
 r radio play\, “Antonia’s Homefront” built around the letters she received
  from her father in Burma during WWII has recently been produced on<a href
 ='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Antonia-M
 atthew.jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='alignright size-th
 umbnail wp-image-4123' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content
 /uploads/2023/09/Antonia-Matthew-150x150.jpg' alt='' width='150' height='1
 50' /></a> WFHB By Richard Fish and won a Gold Award in “Hear Now Audio Fi
 ction and Arts Festival.” She is a member of the Writers Guild of Blooming
 ton and a student of Women Writing for Change\, Bloomington</p>\n<p> </p>
 \n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'><strong>Shana Ritter
 </strong>’s poetry and short stories have appeared in various journals and
  magazines including Lilith\, Fifth Wednesday and Georgetown Review. Her c
 hapbook\, <em>Stairs of Separation</em> was published by Finishing<a href=
 'https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Shana-Ritt
 er-2023.jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='alignright size-t
 humbnail wp-image-4129' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-conten
 t/uploads/2023/09/Shana-Ritter-2023-150x150.jpg' alt='' width='150' height
 ='150' /></a> Line Press. <em>In the Time of Leaving</em>\, a novel of exi
 le and resilience\, set in late 15th century Spain\, was published in 2019
 . Shana has been awarded the Indiana Individual Artist Grant on multiple o
 ccasions.</p>\n</BODY></HTML>
