UID:ai1ec-4148@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020723Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild @ Bloomington presents\n\nPoetry book launch 
 reading by Chicago poet\nDina Elenbogen\n \nIn addition to her latest book
 \, Shore (Glass Lyre Press\, 2023)\, DINA ELENBOGEN has authored the poetr
 y collection\, Apples of the Earth (Spuyten Duyvil\, NY)\, and the memoir\
 , Drawn from Water: an American poet\, an Ethiopian Family\, an Israeli St
 ory (BkMkPress\, University of Missouri). She has received fellowships fro
 m the Illinois Arts Council and the Ragdale Foundation. Her work has appea
 red in magazines and anthologies\, such as Fury: Women’s Lived Experience 
 During the Trump Era (Pact Press)\, City of the Big shoulders (University 
 of Iowa Press)\, Beyond Lament (Northwestern University Press)\, Lit Hub\,
  Bellevue Literary Review\, Prairie Schooner\, Cimarron Review\, Poet Lore
 \, december\, Woven Tale Press\, The Examined Life Journal\, Patterson Lit
 erary Review\, Connecticut River Review\, Rhino\, New City Chicago\, and R
 eform Jewish Quarterly. She holds an MFA in poetry from the Iowa Writers’ 
 Workshop\, and teaches creative writing at the University of Chicago Write
 r’s Studio.\n\nThe reading will be followed by an author Q&A and book sign
 ing
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20231023T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20231023T200000
