 c-event-avatar alignleft timely'><img src='https://writersguildbloomington
 .com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/flying-books.jpg' width='276' height='183'
  /></div><h3 class='yiv2764348631MsoNormal' style='text-align: center\;'>T
 he Writers Guild @ Bloomington presents</h3>\n<p style='text-align: center
 \;'>\n<h2 class='yiv2764348631MsoNormal' style='text-align: center\;'>Poet
 ry book launch reading by Chicago poet</h2>\n<h1 class='yiv2764348631MsoNo
 rmal' style='text-align: center\;'>Dina Elenbogen</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p class
 ='yiv2764348631MsoNormal' style='text-align: center\;'>In addition to her 
 latest book\, <i>Shore </i>(Glass Lyre Press\, 2023)\,<strong> DINA ELENBO
 GEN</strong> has authored the poetry collection\, <i>Apples of the Earth</
 i> (Spuyten Duyvil\, NY)\, and the memoir\, <i>Drawn from Water: an Americ
 an poet\, an Ethiopian Family\, an Israeli Story</i> (BkMkPress\, Universi
 ty of Missouri). She has received fellowships from the Illinois Arts Counc
 il and the Ragdale Foundation. Her work has appeared in magazines and anth
 ologies\, such as <i>Fury: Women’s Lived Experience During the Trump Era</
 i> (Pact Press)\, <i>City of the Big shoulders</i> (University of Iowa Pre
 ss)\, Beyond Lament (Northwestern University Press)\, <i>Lit Hub</i>\, <i>
 Bellevue Literary Review</i>\, <i>Prairie Schooner</i>\, <i>Cimarron Revie
 w</i>\, <i>Poet Lore</i>\, <i>december</i>\, <i>Woven Tale Press</i>\, <i>
 The Examined Life Journal</i>\, <i>Patterson Literary Review</i>\, <i>Conn
 ecticut River Review</i>\, <i>Rhino</i>\, <i>New City Chicago</i>\, and <i
 >Reform Jewish Quarterly</i>. She holds an MFA in poetry from the Iowa Wri
 ters’ Workshop\, and teaches creative writing at the University of Chicago
  Writer’s Studio.</p>\n<p class='yiv2764348631MsoNormal' style='text-align
 : center\;'>\n<p class='yiv2764348631MsoNormal' style='text-align: center\
 ;'><em><strong>The reading will be followed by an author Q&A and book sign
 ing</strong></em></p>\n</BODY></HTML>
