 .com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/DisappearingProse-300x150-1.jpg' width='30
 0' height='150' /></div><h1><a href='https://writersguildbloomington.com/w
 p-content/uploads/2023/01/504615f2-606c-444c-9ec3-ce3c958d1a3b.sized-1000x
 1000-3.jpeg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter size-
 medium wp-image-3884' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/
 uploads/2023/01/504615f2-606c-444c-9ec3-ce3c958d1a3b.sized-1000x1000-3-300
 x140.jpeg' alt='' width='300' height='140' srcset='https://writersguildblo
 omington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/504615f2-606c-444c-9ec3-ce3c958d1a
 3b.sized-1000x1000-3-300x140.jpeg 300w\, https://writersguildbloomington.c
 om/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/504615f2-606c-444c-9ec3-ce3c958d1a3b.sized-1
 000x1000-3-768x359.jpeg 768w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-cont
 ent/uploads/2023/01/504615f2-606c-444c-9ec3-ce3c958d1a3b.sized-1000x1000-3
 -750x350.jpeg 750w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/upload
 s/2023/01/504615f2-606c-444c-9ec3-ce3c958d1a3b.sized-1000x1000-3-642x300.j
 peg 642w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/
 504615f2-606c-444c-9ec3-ce3c958d1a3b.sized-1000x1000-3.jpeg 933w' sizes='a
 uto\, (max-width: 300px) 100vw\, 300px' /></a></h1>\n<h1></h1>\n<h1 style=
 'text-align: center\;'>Writers Guild at Bloomington member</h1>\n<h1 style
 ='text-align: center\;'>T. Newyear</h1>\n<h2 style='text-align: center\;'>
 Rewilding Utopia: An interactive talk + book event</h2>\n<p style='text-al
 ign: center\;'>at</p>\n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>Morgenstern’s</h3>
 \n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>Nov 10 6:30 PM</h3>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir='
 ltr' style='text-align: center\;'>Future Heartland: Indiana Author Release
 s Starfall\, a New Novel Series Exploring the History and Future of a Midw
 estern Utopia</p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'><b> </b></p>\n<p dir='l
 tr' style='text-align: center\;'>The first novel in a four-book\, history-
 meets-cli-fi series drops November 7\, 2023 with its launch event at Morge
 nstern’s Books in Bloomington\, IN on November 10\, 2023.</p>\n<p style='t
 ext-align: center\;'><b> </b></p>\n<p dir='ltr' style='text-align: center\
 ;'>Starfall weaves together the pleasures and romance of historical fictio
 n\, unfolding in the same era as Bridgerton but among a very different mil
 ieu\, while reveling in double-edged future tech dreams that pay tribute t
 o the sci-fi of Ursula LeGuin and Vernor Vinge. These often disparate genr
 es use different conventions to achieve the same goal: questioning where w
 e are now\, how we relate to each other\, and what our lives mean.</p>\n<p
  style='text-align: center\;'><b> </b></p>\n<p dir='ltr' style='text-align
 : center\;'>Like many before her\, author <a id='m_5692554532953960193OWA7
 e7f6f67-6bd1-3982-bc6e-d7b8e8043a3b' href='http://www.newyearmedia.com/' t
 arget='_blank' rel='noopener' data-saferedirecturl='https://www.google.com
 /url?q=http://www.newyearmedia.com/&source=gmail&ust=1696960329251000&usg=
 AOvVaw1JKNJVSNILXz5dP-ekJzip'>T. Newyear</a> stumbled into New Harmony\, I
 ndiana more than a decade ago and couldn’t believe her eyes. The small\, s
 ecluded Indiana town had a sizable collection of 17th-century Italian pain
 tings hanging in its town library. It had a labyrinth of trimmed bushes at
  the edge of town. It had quite a pedigree\, including getting namechecked
  by Lord Byron and Mary Shelley.</p>\n<p dir='ltr' style='text-align: cent
 er\;'>Her explorations over a decade resulted in Starfall (<a href='http:/
 /starfallbook.info/' target='_blank' rel='noopener' data-saferedirecturl='
 https://www.google.com/url?q=http://starfallbook.info&source=gmail&ust=169
 6960329251000&usg=AOvVaw2gi92hvj_KWmc7EQzPeLXX'>starfallbook.info</a>)\, a
  sweeping tale set in both the 1820s heyday of New Harmony’s utopian exper
 iment and in the not-too-distant future post-climate change. In both narra
 tive threads\, a woman lands in the town and attempts to unravel a mystery
 : there are strange pools that form in the woods when the stars fall.</p>
 \n<h4 dir='ltr' style='text-align: center\;'>About T. Newyear</h4>\n<p dir
 ='ltr' style='text-align: center\;'><b> </b></p>\n<p dir='ltr' style='text
 -align: center\;'>For T. Newyear\, the past and the future are two pages i
 n the same book. Combining extensive research and emotional clarity\, she 
 writes historical fantasies and scientific romances (as H.G. Wells put it)
  that explore our complex human and technological relationships\, our conn
 ections to what’s greater than us\, and our understanding of the past. By 
 playing with historical movements and events\, tech and its impact\, and g
 ood ol’ human foibles\, she crafts long-form stories that envelope readers
  in another world or era–and helps them feel through our current dilemmas.
 </p>\n<p dir='ltr' style='text-align: center\;'><b> </b></p>\n<p dir='ltr'
  style='text-align: center\;'>A native of the Midwestern US\, Newyear grew
  up in small towns and fading cities\, inspired by nature and culture\, tr
 adition and radicalism in equal measure. She lived extensively in Russia\,
  traveled alone across Siberia and Mongolia\, and learned how the other si
 de of the world related to her home turf. With a doctorate in history and 
 area studies\, she has a profound interest in exploring the details and li
 ved experiences of the past\, and imagining how those lost moments speak t
 o our collective future.</p>\n<p dir='ltr' style='text-align: center\;'><b
  id='m_5692554532953960193docs-internal-guid-7642eff1-7fff-2d78-53ea-61a34
 76dd971'><br />\nFor more info and to sign up for her newsletter\, go to <
 a href='http://newyearmedia.com/' target='_blank' rel='noopener' data-safe
 redirecturl='https://www.google.com/url?q=http://newyearmedia.com&source=g
 mail&ust=1696960329251000&usg=AOvVaw2Bsqf_uHx7reBBstTuMn65'>newyearmedia.c
 om</a></b></p>\n<p dir='ltr'><strong>Other Starfall Events:</strong></p>\n
 <p dir='ltr'>November 11: Fallen Leaf Books | Nashville\, IN | 1-4 PM</p>
 \n<p dir='ltr'>November 16: Bartholomew Co. Library | Columbus\, IN | 6:30
  PM</p>\n<p dir='ltr'>January 20\, 2024: Monroe Co Historical Society | Bl
 oomington\, IN | 1:30 PM</p>\n<p dir='ltr' style='text-align: center\;'>Cl
 ick <a href='http://bit.ly/starfallbook'><strong>HERE</strong></a> for ful
 l press release</p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>\n</BODY></HTML>
X-INSTANT-EVENT:1
