SUMMARY:First Sunday Prose Reading and Open Mic
URL:https://writersguildbloomington.com/event/first-sunday-prose-reading-an
 d-open-mic-16/
X-COST-TYPE:free
X-WP-IMAGES-URL:thumbnail\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/u
 ploads/2019/08/imagesCA75KN6E-OPEN-MOUTH-150x150.jpg\;150\;150\;1\,medium\
 ;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/imagesCA75
 KN6E-OPEN-MOUTH.jpg\;202\;249\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><div class='ai1e
 c-event-avatar alignleft timely'><img src='https://writersguildbloomington
 .com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/imagesCA75KN6E-OPEN-MOUTH.jpg' width='202'
  height='249' /></div><h1 style='text-align: center\;'>First Sunday Prose 
 Reading and Open Mic</h1>\n<h2 style='text-align: center\;'>Presented by t
 he Writers Guild</h2>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>\n<h3 style='text-a
 lign: center\;'>The featured readers are:</h3>\n<h2 style='text-align: cen
 ter\;'>Molly Gleeson</h2>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>and</p>\n<h2 st
 yle='text-align: center\;'>Claire Arbogast</h2>\n<h3 style='text-align: ce
 nter\;'>Sunday\, Dec 3\, 2023</h3>\n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>3:00 
 to 5:00</h3>\n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>Morgenstern’s</h3>\n<h3 sty
 le='text-align: center\;'>849 S Auto Mall Road</h3>\n<p style='text-align:
  center\;'>\n<h4 style='text-align: center\;'>Come early to sign up for Op
 en Mic!</h4>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>\n<p style='text-align: cent
 er\;'>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>Molly Gleeson was nominated for a 
 Pushcart Prize for her story\, ‘Meishi\, Furo\, Neru’\, which won first pl
 ace in The Midnight Oil Magazine’s short story contest in 2020. She has al
 so been published in The Apeiron Review\, Crab Fat Literary Magazine\, and
  Brush Talks\, among others. Molly spent seven years teaching English in C
 hina\, Saudi Arabia\, and Japan and is now happy to be back in her hometow
 n of Bloomington\, Indiana. She is working on her second novel\, which she
  hopes will not remain as unpublished as her first.</p>\n<p><a href='https
 ://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/gleeson-rotated.
 jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter wp-image-4208
  size-medium' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/
 2023/11/gleeson-225x300.jpg' alt='' width='225' height='300' srcset='https
 ://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/gleeson-225x300.
 jpg 225w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/
 gleeson-rotated.jpg 240w' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 225px) 100vw\, 225px' 
 /></a></p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>\n<p style='text-align: center
 \;'>Claire Arbogast is the author of the novel<em> If Not the Whole Truth<
 /em> [due to be published by the end of next year] and <em>Leave the Dogs 
 at Home: A Memoir</em> published by Indiana University Press. <em>Leave th
 e Dogs at Home</em> was winner of the 2016 AAUP Public and Secondary Schoo
 l Library Selection and was called an “excellent choice” by the Library Jo
 urnal—you can find it on the local author shelf here at Morganstern.</p>\n
 <p style='text-align: center\;'>Researching and writing <em>If Not the Who
 le Truth</em>—a novel about a young woman who struggles to ferret out her 
 place in the counterculture of the late 1960s era only to find in 2022 Ame
 rica that everything she holds dear\, even her own life\, is in jeopardy—r
 e-activated Claire politically. She became a Planned Parenthood escort (sh
 ort-lived as Indiana’s abortion ban was reinstated)\, joined the National 
 Organization of Women\, the Feminist Majority Foundation\, and PEN America
 . She is a member of the Writers Guild at Bloomington\, the Indiana Writer
 s Center\, the Chicago Writers Association\, a grateful past participant o
 f Women Writing for a Change\, and a recurring donor to the Susan A. Moke 
 Endowment Fund.</p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>She has a B.A. in jou
 rnalism from Indiana University and was awarded the 2009–2010 Greer Artist
  Fellowship Award and a scholarship to the 2009 The Ropewalk Writer’s Conf
 erence Master’s Class.</p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>Claire’s books
 \, essays\, and short fiction\, as well as blog posts found on <a href='ht
 tp://www.clairearbogast.com/blog-inside-stories'>www.clairearbogast.com/bl
 og-inside-stories</a>\, challenge attitudes and start conversations.</p>\n
 <p><a href='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11
 /arbogast.jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter siz
 e-full wp-image-4209' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/
 uploads/2023/11/arbogast.jpg' alt='' width='166' height='241' /></a></p>\n
 </BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
