 0.jpg' alt='' width='212' height='300' srcset='https://writersguildbloomin
 gton.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/matthew-212x300.jpg 212w\, https://wri
 tersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/matthew.jpg 441w' size
 s='auto\, (max-width: 212px) 100vw\, 212px' /></a></p>\n<p style='text-ali
 gn: center\;'>A retired teacher of English and photography\, <strong>Roger
  Pfingston</strong> is the recipient of a Creative Writing Fellowship from
  the National Endowment for the Arts and two PEN Syndicated Fiction Awards
 . He is the author of Something Iridescent\, a collection of poetry and fi
 ction\, and five chapbooks: Nesting\, Earthbound\, Singing to the Garden\,
  A Day Marked for Telling\, and What’s Given. His poems have appeared in a
  wide range of publications in print and online\, including I-70 Review\, 
 Poet Lore\, Poetry East\, Sheila-Na-Gig\, Innisfree Poetry Journal\, and T
 ed Kooser’s column\, American Life in Poetry.</p>\n<p><a href='https://wri
 tersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/pfingston.png'><img lo
 ading='lazy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4219
 ' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/pfin
 gston-230x300.png' alt='' width='230' height='300' srcset='https://writers
 guildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/pfingston-230x300.png 230w
 \, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/pfingsto
 n-785x1024.png 785w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploa
 ds/2023/11/pfingston-768x1001.png 768w\, https://writersguildbloomington.c
 om/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/pfingston.png 1132w' sizes='auto\, (max-widt
 h: 230px) 100vw\, 230px' /></a></p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'><stro
 ng>Eric Rensberger</strong> is a local poet who has lived in Bloomington s
 ince 1979. He has a long acquaintance with Jenny Kander and appreciates he
 r steady advocacy for poetry in our community.</p>\n<p><a href='https://wr
 itersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/rensberger.jpg'><img 
 loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter size-medium wp-image-42
 20' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/re
