UID:ai1ec-4236@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:First Sunday Prose Reading and Open Mic\nPresented by\nWriters 
 Guild at Bloomington\nFeatured Authors\nSharon Pugh\nand\nRichard H. Duris
 en\nfrom the Dec/Jan 2023\nRyder Special Bloomington Fiction Issue\n\nSund
 ay\, Jan 7\, 2024\n3:00 to 5:00\nMorgenstern’s\n849 S Auto Mall Road\nCome
  early to sign up for Open Mic!\nSharon Pugh is a long-time resident of Bl
 oomington and emerita faculty member of the IU School of Education. Her fi
 ction has appeared in a previous edition of the Ryder as well as in severa
 l literary journals. Her short story collection\, Old Technologies\, is av
 ailable on Amazon.\n\nRichard Durisen is a Professor Emeritus of Astronomy
  at Indiana University Bloomington. He retired in 2010 so he could devote 
 time to creative writing\, including poetry\, short stories\, and now a ne
 arly finished novel. Most of this work is in speculative genres. The websi
 te durisen.com offers a sampler of his publications in various print and o
 nline venues. For the story he is reading\, as for many others over the pa
 st decade or so\, I want to acknowledge thoughtful critiques and encourage
 ment from the members of Our Writing League\, a Bloomington writers group.
 \n\n 
