BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4251@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Trigger Warnings\nBook Launch\n \n112 W 6th Street\nBackspace a
 t Bonne Fete\n6 p.m.\nThursday January 18th\, 2024\n\nFriday January 19th\
 , 2024\n4:30-6 p.m.\nMonroe County Public Library Auditorium\n303 E Kirkwo
 od Avenue\n\nSaturday January 20th\, 2024\n12-2 p.m.\nMorgenstern Books\n8
 49 S Auto Mall Rd\n\n\n\nTrigger Warnings\, edited by Joan Hawkins and Kal
 ynn Brower– is an anthology of writings about survival and escape from sex
 ual assault– written by members of The Writers Guild at Bloomington\, is o
 ut.\nThe Book Launch will be held Thursday Jan 18 at BackSpace  (in Bonne 
 Fête\, 112 W 6th St) at 6 p.m. Dr. Maria Hamilton Abegunde\, Tom Bitters\,
  Kalynn Brower\, Joan Hawkins\, Tonia Matthew\, and Hiromi Yoshida will be
  the featured readers. (Kalynn is coming back to Bloomington for the event
 ).  Music by Ortet. Books will be available for purchase and signing.\nOn 
 Friday January 19th from 4:30-6 PM there will be a reading at the auditori
 um at the Monroe County Public Library.\nThere will also be a one-on-one e
 vent and book signing at Morgenstern Books on Sat Jan 20 from 12-2 PM.\nJo
 an Hawkins is going to try to organize another reading on campus at the Co
 llege Arts and Humanities Institute\, so that other authors in the antholo
 gy will have a chance to read their work. Please check the newsletter and 
 the website later for further information on this.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240118T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240120T181500
