 ngs</em></h1>\n<h1 style='text-align: center\;'>Book Launch</h1>\n<p> </p>
 \n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'><strong>112 W 6th Street<br />\nBackspa
 ce at Bonne Fete<br />\n6 p.m.<br />\nThursday January 18th\, 2024</strong
 ></h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'><strong>Friday January
  19th\, 2024<br />\n4:30-6 p.m.<br />\nMonroe County Public Library Audito
 rium<br />\n303 E Kirkwood Avenue</strong></h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3 style='tex
 t-align: center\;'><strong>Saturday January 20th\, 2024<br />\n12-2 p.m.<b
 r />\nMorgenstern Books</strong><br />\n<strong>849 S Auto Mall Rd</strong
 ></h3>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div style='text-align: center\;'>\n<h4>
 <strong>Trigger Warnings</strong>\, edited by Joan Hawkins and Kalynn Brow
 er– is an anthology of writings about survival and escape from sexual assa
 ult– written by members of The Writers Guild at Bloomington\, is out.</h4>
 \n<h4>The Book Launch will be held Thursday Jan 18 at BackSpace  (in Bonne
  Fête\, 112 W 6<sup>th</sup> St) at 6 p.m. Dr. Maria Hamilton Abegunde\, T
 om Bitters\, Kalynn Brower\, Joan Hawkins\, Tonia Matthew\, and Hiromi Yos
 hida will be the featured readers. (Kalynn is coming back to Bloomington f
 or the event).  Music by Ortet. Books will be available for purchase and s
 igning.</h4>\n<h4>On Friday January 19th from 4:30-6 PM there will be a re
 ading at the auditorium at the Monroe County Public Library.</h4>\n<h4>The
 re will also be a one-on-one event and book signing at Morgenstern Books o
 n Sat Jan 20 from 12-2 PM.</h4>\n<h4>Joan Hawkins is going to try to organ
 ize another reading on campus at the College Arts and Humanities Institute
 \, so that other authors in the anthology will have a chance to read their
  work. Please check the newsletter and the website later for further infor
 mation on this.</h4>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h4 class='yj6qo'></h4>\n<div class=
 'adL'></div>\n</div>\n<div class='yj6qo'></div>\n<div class='adL'></div>\n
 </BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
