 > </p>\n<p><strong>Joan Hawkins </strong>is Professor of Cinema and Media 
 Studies at IU Bloomington. Her creative work and poetry have appeared in <
 em>Sand\, The Ryder\, Avalanches of Poetry\, Fevers of the Mind\, Plath Pr
 ofiles\, n+1\, </em>and the <em>Performing Arts Journal.</em> A book of sh
 ort memoir pieces\, <em>School and Suicide</em>\, was published by Alien B
 uddha Press in 2022.  With jazz-collage artist Kyle Quass\, she released a
  spoken word and sound collage CD\, <em>Pragis. </em>A chapbook of poetry\
 , <em>The Burroughs Hour\,</em> was published in 2023 by Grind Stone Press
 .</p>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
