DESCRIPTION:First Sunday Prose Reading and Open Mic\nPresented by\nWriters 
 Guild at Bloomington\nIn Honor of Women’s History Month\nFeatured Readers
 \nGladys DeVane\nand\nBeau Vallance\nSunday\, March 3\, 2024\nPLEASE NOTE 
 THE VENUE AND TIME CHANGE\n2pm to 3:30pm\nThe Juniper Gallery\n615 W. Kirk
 wood Avenue\nCome early to sign up for Open Mic!\n \n\nGladys DeVane—Profe
 ssor Emerita\, Indiana University—is a storyteller\, actor\, and writer. S
 he has written four original plays\, numerous one-person shows\, and a boo
 k—Come Sit with Me: Life in Poetry\, Prose\, and Plays. Gladys is co-found
 er of Resilience Productions INC\, a theatrical company that researches\, 
 writes\, and produces plays—inspired by actual events—that tell the Africa
 n American story.\nGladys DeVane’s book\, Come Sit with Me: Life in Poetry
 \, Prose\, and Plays\, will be available for sale. Cash and checks accepte
 d.\n\nBeau Vallance is retired from art-museum work and IU teacher educati
 on. Her writing lately has been for a summer newspaper in Michigan\, the I
 U Emeriti House life-writing workshop\, a year-long StoryWorth project\, t
 wo pieces in The Ryder\, very long emails to friends\, and a draft of her 
 own obituary. Her writing has gotten quite free-wheeling since she’s no lo
 nger writing for professional journals\, but she had a huge resume of arti
 cles on such exciting topics as the hidden curriculum\, curriculum theory\
 , and museum education. It’s more fun now.
