BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4365@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:wfiu.org/poetsweave\,
DESCRIPTION:The Poets Weave reaches a milestone this Sunday when its 1\,000
 th episode airs on March 31.\nThe Poets Weave airs Sundays at 3:54 p.m. on
  WFIU and 5:54 p.m. on WFIU2. Episodes are\nalso available on The Poets We
 ave website\, wfiu.org/poetsweave\, and through major podcast\nplatforms.
 \nAntonia Matthew\nEpisode 1\,000 of The Poets Weave will feature Antonia 
 Matthew reading “Rabbit Mysteries” and\nother poems with spring themes. Ma
 tthew has lived in Bloomington since 1968 and has been a\npart of the Five
  Women Poets writing workshop for 39 years. She has been published in smal
 l\nmagazines\, self-published a chapbook on her mother’s Alzheimer’s\, and
  has written a play about\nher experiences as a child in World War II Engl
 and.\n\nAbout The Poets Weave\nThe Poets Weave is a weekly five-minute pro
 gram of poetry reading hosted by Bloomington-\nbased poet Romayne Rubinas 
 Dorsey\, a senior lecturer at Indiana University.\n\nThe Poets Weave was c
 reated in 2006 by Jenny Kander\, who produced and hosted the program\nunti
 l 2009. After moving from South Africa to Bloomington in 1992\, Kander pro
 mised herself\nthat she would take poetry classes—something she never had 
 time for previously. This began her\ninfluence in the Bloomington communit
 y as the “poetry lady\,” a title she says she adores.\nJenny Kander photo 
 by Nadav Kander\n \n 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240331T154500
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240331T164500
LOCATION:The Poets Weave airs Sundays at 3:54 p.m. on WFIU and 5:54 p.m. on
  WFIU2. Episodes are also available on The Poets Weave website\, wfiu.org/
 poetsweave\, and through major podcast platforms.
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The Poets Weave 1000th Episode!!!
URL:https://writersguildbloomington.com/event/the-poets-weave-1000th-episod
 e/
X-COST-TYPE:free
X-WP-IMAGES-URL:thumbnail\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/u
 ploads/2023/11/matthew-212x300.jpg\;212\;300\,medium\;https://writersguild
 bloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/matthew-212x300.jpg\;212\;300\,
 large\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/matt
 hew-212x300.jpg\;212\;300\,full\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-co
 ntent/uploads/2023/11/matthew-212x300.jpg\;212\;300
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><h3 style='text-
 align: left\;'>The Poets Weave reaches a milestone this Sunday when its 1\
 ,000th episode airs on March 31.</h3>\n<h3 style='text-align: left\;'>The 
 Poets Weave airs Sundays at 3:54 p.m. on WFIU and 5:54 p.m. on WFIU2. Epis
 odes are<br />\nalso available on The Poets Weave website\, wfiu.org/poets
 weave\, and through major podcast<br />\nplatforms.</h3>\n<figure id='atta
 chment_4218' aria-describedby='caption-attachment-4218' style='width: 212p
 x' class='wp-caption aligncenter'><a href='https://writersguildbloomington
 .com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/matthew.jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding=
 'async' class='size-medium wp-image-4218' src='https://writersguildbloomin
 gton.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/matthew-212x300.jpg' alt='' width='212
 ' height='300' srcset='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uplo
 ads/2023/11/matthew-212x300.jpg 212w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com
 /wp-content/uploads/2023/11/matthew.jpg 441w' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 21
 2px) 100vw\, 212px' /></a><figcaption id='caption-attachment-4218' class='
 wp-caption-text'>Antonia Matthew</figcaption></figure>\n<h3>Episode 1\,000
  of The Poets Weave will feature Antonia Matthew reading “Rabbit Mysteries
 ” and<br />\nother poems with spring themes. Matthew has lived in Blooming
 ton since 1968 and has been a<br />\npart of the Five Women Poets writing 
 workshop for 39 years. She has been published in small<br />\nmagazines\, 
 self-published a chapbook on her mother’s Alzheimer’s\, and has written a 
 play about<br />\nher experiences as a child in World War II England.</h3>
 \n<h3 style='text-align: center\;'>\nAbout The Poets Weave</h3>\n<h3 style
 ='text-align: left\;'>The Poets Weave is a weekly five-minute program of p
 oetry reading hosted by Bloomington-<br />\nbased poet Romayne Rubinas Dor
 sey\, a senior lecturer at Indiana University.</h3>\n<h3 style='text-align
 : left\;'>\nThe Poets Weave was created in 2006 by Jenny Kander\, who prod
 uced and hosted the program<br />\nuntil 2009. After moving from South Afr
 ica to Bloomington in 1992\, Kander promised herself<br />\nthat she would
  take poetry classes—something she never had time for previously. This beg
 an her<br />\ninfluence in the Bloomington community as the “poetry lady\,
