BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4376@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents Alex Gold: Stuck on Repea
 t\nA fun-filled classroom adventure where the audience gets to make all th
 e decisions! See it on stage April 26 – May 12 at the Waldron Auditorium.
 \n11-year-old Alex Gold needs to repeat the 6th grade – maybe he shouldn’t
  have spent so much time watching superhero movies\, playing adventure gam
 es\, and drifting off into his own action-packed daydreams. Luckily\, Alex
  has surrounded himself with some trusted friends (you\, the audience!) to
  help him make the best choices to succeed! This one-of-a-kind classroom c
 omedy blends improv and audience interaction\, proving every day is an opp
 ortunity for reinvention.\nFor a detailed performance schedule\, please vi
 sit our website.\nLearn more and find tickets at https://seeconstellation.
 org/kids/alex-gold/
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240426T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240512T160000
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Alex Gold: Stuck on Repeat
URL:https://writersguildbloomington.com/event/alex-gold-stuck-on-repeat/
X-COST-TYPE:free
X-WP-IMAGES-URL:thumbnail\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/u
 ploads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Social-Ad-300x300.png\;300\;300\,medium\
