 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><h2 style='text-
 align: center\;'></h2>\n<h2 style='text-align: left\;'><span style='color:
  #ff9900\;'>Constellation Stage & Screen presents Alex Gold: Stuck on Repe
 at</span></h2>\n<p style='text-align: left\;'><strong>A fun-filled classro
 om adventure where the audience gets to make all the decisions! See it on 
 stage April 26 – May 12 at the Waldron Auditorium.</strong></p>\n<p style=
 'text-align: left\;'><a href='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-conte
 nt/uploads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Social-Ad.png'><img loading='lazy' d
 ecoding='async' class='size-medium wp-image-4377 alignleft' src='https://w
 ritersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-S
 ocial-Ad-300x300.png' alt='' width='300' height='300' srcset='https://writ
 ersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Soci
 al-Ad-300x300.png 300w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/up
 loads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Social-Ad-150x150.png 150w\, https://writ
 ersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Soci
 al-Ad-768x768.png 768w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/up
 loads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Social-Ad-270x270.png 270w\, https://writ
 ersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Soci
 al-Ad-230x230.png 230w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/up
 loads/2024/04/Alex-Gold-Tile-for-Social-Ad.png 801w' sizes='auto\, (max-wi
 dth: 300px) 100vw\, 300px' /></a>11-year-old Alex Gold needs to repeat the
  6th grade – maybe he shouldn’t have spent so much time watching superhero
  movies\, playing adventure games\, and drifting off into his own action-p
 acked daydreams. Luckily\, Alex has surrounded himself with some trusted f
 riends (you\, the audience!) to help him make the best choices to succeed!
  This one-of-a-kind classroom comedy blends improv and audience interactio
 n\, proving every day is an opportunity for reinvention.</p>\n<p style='te
 xt-align: left\;'>For a detailed performance schedule\, please visit our w
 ebsite.</p>\n<p style='text-align: left\;'>Learn more and find tickets at 
 <a href='https://seeconstellation.org/kids/alex-gold/'>https://seeconstell
 ation.org/kids/alex-gold/</a></p>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4363@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Last Sunday Poetry & Open Mic\nApril 28th\, 2024\n7 – 8:30 p.m.
 \nMorgenstern Books at 849 S Auto Mall Rd\n\n\nThe Writers Guild @ Bloomin
 gton presents Last Sunday Poetry & Open Mic\, featuring Patsy Rahn and Ros
 aleen Crowley.\n\nPATSY RAHN’s poetry and prose have been published in var
 ious journals and anthologies. Her nonfiction has been published in the Un
 ited States and in Britain. Her first book of poetry\, The Grainy Wet Soul
 \, was independently published in 2018. In 2021 she received the People’s 
 Choice Award from the 5th Open Eurasion Literary Festival of Festivals “LI
 FT”. She continues to give public readings and has read for festivals\, li
 terary events\, and with the Bloomington Symphony Orchestra.\nAuthor websi
 te: www.patsyrahn.com\n\nROSALEEN CROWLEY is a poet\, artist and educator.
  She is a graduate of University College Cork\, Ireland. Currently she is 
 Co-founder/President\, Carmel Creative Writers\, Inc and past president/in
 terest group leader of the Writing Group\, International Women Indiana. Sh
 e is the author of six poetry books\, her most recent being Be Prepared To
  Be Luminous\, a collection of poems written in Indiana. The book has four
  sections: Surroundings\, People\, Gratitude\, and Contemplation. Rosaleen
  is enrolled as a student in the MFA Creative Writing-Poetry program at Bu
 tler University.\nAmazon author page:\nhttps://www.amazon.com/…/Rosaleen…/
 author/B08P3T3ZQ4…\n\n\nEmerging poets who need a supportive audience\, an
 d established poets\, who want to promote published works: Sign up for ope
 n mic! Your words are precious.\n\nThe Writers Guild @ Bloomington is comm
 itted to diversity\, equity\, and inclusivity.\n\n\nhttps://writersguildbl
 oomington.com/
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240428T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240428T203000
