BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4384@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:First Sunday Prose Reading Series\nFeaturing Freda Love Smith a
 nd Jeremy Reed\nSunday\, May 5\, 2024\n2-3:30pm\nThe Juniper Art Gallery  
 615 W. Kirkwood Avenue\nFree and Open to the Public  $5 suggested donation
  to the venue\nThe Gallery also has a full-service cafe! Please no outside
  food or drink.\n \n\nFreda Love Smith is a writer and retired drummer. He
 r memoir\, I Quit Everything\, explores addiction\, intoxication\, and the
  twilight of her musical career. Her first book\, Red Velvet Underground\,
  documents a year of cooking lessons with her son and reminisces about dru
 mming with bands including Blake Babies and Mysteries of Life. Freda grew 
 up in Bloomington and currently lives in Evanston\, Illinois.\n \n \n \nJe
 remy Reed is a PhD Candidate in the Indiana University-Bloomington Departm
 ent of Folklore and Ethnomusicology. At this event you’ll hear him read so
 me excerpts from his forthcoming dissertation on festivals and the public 
 sphere in Jordan. If you think you’ve seen him before it’s likely that you
  have seen him running around as a production volunteer and former staff m
 ember at the Lotus Education and Arts Foundation\; have seen him pull out 
 a freshly baked loaf of bread from his bag\; or have seen him zipping arou
 nd on a bright orange bike. In an effort to prove that dissertations can b
 e interesting\, he’s selected sections that deal with him grappling with p
 ublic rumors\, a national festival\, and the limits of what is and is not 
 allowed to be said in public in Jordan.\n \n 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240505T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240505T153000
LOCATION:Juniper Art Gallery @ 615 W. Kirkwood Avenue
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:First Sunday Prose Reading Series
