BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4389@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION: \nSunday\, May 26\, 2024\n7:00-8:30 pm\nMorgenstern’s Bookstor
 e & Cafe\nLast Sunday Poetry & Open Mic FEATURING Jonathan S. Baker & Tere
 sa Roy\n\nThe Writers Guild @ Bloomington presents Last Sunday Poetry & Op
 en Mic\, featuring Evansville poets Jonathan S Baker and Teresa Roy.\nJONA
 THAN S BAKER lives and works in Evansville\, Indiana\, where they are the 
 host and organizer of Poetry Speaks\, Indiana’s longest running poetry ser
 ies. They are also co-editor at The Grind Stone and editor-in-chief at Pur
 e Sleeze Press. They have published 12 books of poetry including Long Nigh
 ts in Stoplight City (Between Shadows Press\, 2023)\, Pressure (Two Key Cu
 stoms\, 2023)\, Cock of the Walk (Laughing Ronin Press\, 2022)\, and Raise
 d in the TV (The Grind Stone\, 2022).\nThese books and more are available 
 at:\nhttps://www.amazon.com/…/Jonathan…/author/B005S5L1PK\nEvansville resi
 dent TERESA ROY is a decades-long participant in the area’s poetry landsca
 pe. Published in the ancient poetry bibles Kayak and Exquisite Corpse\, an
 d in Nimrod\, she was also a frequent contributor to this century’s Open 2
 4 Hours\, The Round Table.\nShe embraces Robert Graves’ epitaph: “To be a 
 poet is a condition\, not a profession.”\nEmerging poets who need a suppor
 tive audience\, and established poets who want to promote published works:
  Sign up for open mic! Your words are precious. (Time limit: 2-3 min. per 
 open mic participant)\nCome early to sign up for open mic\; to meet and gr
 eet program participants\; and to purchase food and beverages before the 7
 pm cafe closing time.\nThe Writers Guild @ Bloomington is committed to div
 ersity\, equity\, and inclusivity.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240526T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240526T203000
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Last Sunday Poetry & Open Mic – Jonathan S. Baker & Teresa Roy
URL:https://writersguildbloomington.com/event/last-sunday-poetry-open-mic-3
 /
