 g\;300\;273\;1\,large\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uplo
 ads/2024/05/437846403_10161073235854210_3758278246812687781_n-1024x933.jpg
 \;750\;683\;1\,full\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/upload
 s/2024/05/437846403_10161073235854210_3758278246812687781_n.jpg\;2048\;186
 6\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><div class='ai1e
 c-event-avatar alignleft timely'><img src='https://writersguildbloomington
 .com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/437846403_10161073235854210_37582782468126
 87781_n-300x273.jpg' width='300' height='273' /></div><p> </p>\n<h2 style=
 'text-align: center\;'><em><strong>Sunday\, May 26\, 2024</strong></em></h
 2>\n<h2 style='text-align: center\;'><em><strong>7:00-8:30 pm</strong></em
 ></h2>\n<h2 style='text-align: center\;'><em><strong>Morgenstern’s Booksto
 re & Cafe</strong></em></h2>\n<h2>Last Sunday Poetry & Open Mic <span styl
 e='color: #800080\;'>FEATURING</span> Jonathan S. Baker & Teresa Roy</h2>
 \n<p><a href='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/
 05/437846403_10161073235854210_3758278246812687781_n.jpg'><img loading='la
 zy' decoding='async' class='aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4390' src='ht
 tps://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/437846403_101
 61073235854210_3758278246812687781_n-300x273.jpg' alt='' width='300' heigh
 t='273' srcset='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/202
 4/05/437846403_10161073235854210_3758278246812687781_n-300x273.jpg 300w\, 
 https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/437846403_1
 0161073235854210_3758278246812687781_n-1024x933.jpg 1024w\, https://writer
 sguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/437846403_101610732358542
 10_3758278246812687781_n-768x700.jpg 768w\, https://writersguildbloomingto
 n.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/437846403_10161073235854210_3758278246812
 687781_n-1536x1400.jpg 1536w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-cont
 ent/uploads/2024/05/437846403_10161073235854210_3758278246812687781_n.jpg 
 2048w' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 300px) 100vw\, 300px' /></a></p>\n<p>The 
 Writers Guild @ Bloomington presents Last Sunday Poetry & Open Mic\, featu
 ring Evansville poets Jonathan S Baker and Teresa Roy.</p>\n<p><strong>JON
 ATHAN S BAKER</strong> lives and works in Evansville\, Indiana\, where the
 y are the host and organizer of Poetry Speaks\, Indiana’s longest running 
 poetry series. They are also co-editor at The Grind Stone and editor-in-ch
 ief at Pure Sleeze Press. They have published 12 books of poetry including
  Long Nights in Stoplight City (Between Shadows Press\, 2023)\, Pressure (
 Two Key Customs\, 2023)\, Cock of the Walk (Laughing Ronin Press\, 2022)\,
  and Raised in the TV (The Grind Stone\, 2022).</p>\n<p>These books and mo
 re are available at:<br />\n<a href='https://www.amazon.com/stores/author/
 B005S5L1PK' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>https://www.amazon.com/…/Jonath
 an…/author/B005S5L1PK</a></p>\n<p>Evansville resident <strong>TERESA ROY</
 strong> is a decades-long participant in the area’s poetry landscape. Publ
 ished in the ancient poetry bibles Kayak and Exquisite Corpse\, and in Nim
 rod\, she was also a frequent contributor to this century’s Open 24 Hours\
 , The Round Table.<br />\nShe embraces Robert Graves’ epitaph: “To be a po
 et is a condition\, not a profession.”</p>\n<p>Emerging poets who need a s
 upportive audience\, and established poets who want to promote published w
 orks: Sign up for open mic! Your words are precious. (Time limit: 2-3 min.
  per open mic participant)</p>\n<p>Come early to sign up for open mic\; to
  meet and greet program participants\; and to purchase food and beverages 
 before the 7pm cafe closing time.</p>\n<p>The Writers Guild @ Bloomington 
 is committed to diversity\, equity\, and inclusivity.</p>\n<div></div>\n</
 BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
