DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild at Bloomington\nPresents\nFirst Sunday Prose 
 Reading Series\nJune 2\, 2024\nThe Juniper Gallery and Cafe (615 W. Kirkwo
 od)\n2-3:30pm\nThe Writers Guild will honor Pride Month with featured read
 ers David Dunn and Gail Fairfield.\nDavid Dunn is the executive director o
 f PetsAlive in Bloomington\, IN. He is a frequent contributor to Drunk Mon
 keys magazine\, and his most recent piece\, How to Toss a Frisbee That Mig
 ht Also Be a Star\, can be found in their February issue. He is currently 
 (and perpetually) working on his first novel.\nGail Fairfield writes and i
 llustrates children’s stories about Roly Poly. Her images merge the rich c
 olors and fluidity of alcohol ink with photographs of the real dog. The bo
 oks and Gail’s art are available through Amazon\, Barnes & Noble\, Morgens
 tern’s\, and www.gailfairfieldinks.com. Follow Gail Fairfield Inks on Inst
 agram and Facebook.
