X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><p><a href='http
 s://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/The-Break-Tile-
 for-Social-Ad-1.png'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='size-medi
 um wp-image-4401 alignleft' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-co
 ntent/uploads/2024/05/The-Break-Tile-for-Social-Ad-1-300x300.png' alt='' w
 idth='300' height='300' srcset='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-con
 tent/uploads/2024/05/The-Break-Tile-for-Social-Ad-1-300x300.png 300w\, htt
 ps://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/The-Break-Tile
 -for-Social-Ad-1-150x150.png 150w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp
 -content/uploads/2024/05/The-Break-Tile-for-Social-Ad-1-768x768.png 768w\,
  https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/The-Break-
 Tile-for-Social-Ad-1-270x270.png 270w\, https://writersguildbloomington.co
 m/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/The-Break-Tile-for-Social-Ad-1-230x230.png 23
 0w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/The-Br
 eak-Tile-for-Social-Ad-1.png 801w' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 300px) 100vw\
 , 300px' /></a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Constellation Stage & Screen pre
 sents</strong><br />\n<span style='color: #0000ff\;'><strong>The Break: A 
 New Rock Musical<br />\n</strong></span><strong>On stage June 6 – 23 at th
 e Waldron Auditorium</strong></p>\n<p>1 Couple. 30 Days Off. No Rules.</p>
 \n<p>This brand new rock musical from the Emmy-nominated creators of The E
 nlightenment of Percival von Schmootz is a spicy rom com with a healthy do
 se of heart. Sam and Charlie have been together since freshman year of col
 lege. They love each other…but do they? As the marriage question looms\, i
 t’s time to find out what’s holding them back. The two agree to take a 30-
 day break to date other people and at the end of the month they’ll finally
  tie the knot…or will they?</p>\n<p>For a detailed performance schedule\, 
 please visit our website. Featuring Pay What You Will Thursdays (choose yo
 ur own ticket price\, starting as low as $5). Learn more and find tickets 
 at <a href='https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/the-break/'>https://see
 constellation.org/mainstage/the-break/</a></p>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4423@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:OPEN MIC following the features\nTHURSDAY\, JUN 13\n6pm EST\nfe
 aturing poets Joseph Kerschbaum\, Jason Ammerman\, Tony Brewer\nmusic by J
 ulian Douglas and Kyle Quass\nopen mic to follow\n\nSponsored in part by t
 he Indiana Arts Commission\, Bloomington Arts Commission\, and the Bloomin
 gton Urban Enterprise Association\n\n\nJOSEPH KERSCHBAUM’s most recent pub
 lications include Mirror Box (Main St Rag Press\, 2020)\, Distant Shores o
 f a Split Second (Louisiana Literature Press\, 2018)\, and Midnight Sunris
 e just out from Main Street Rag Press. His recent work has appeared in Reu
 nion: The Dallas Review\, Hamilton Stone Review\, The Inflectionist Review
 \, Main Street Rag\, In Parentheses\, and Umbrella Factory. Joseph lives i
 n Bloomington\, Indiana with his family.\n\n\nJASON L. AMMERMAN began his 
 career as a poet in 1989 at the young and impressionable age of sixteen. H
 e crossed paths with great poets who shared the stage with talented and ea
 rth moving poets like Etheridge Knight. During the 90s\, Jason led many po
 etry readings in and around Indianapolis\, becoming involved with the poet
 ry slam scene in the late 90s/early 2000s. In 2008 He formed the Reservoir
  Dogwoods performance troupe along with poets Tony Brewer\, Joseph Kerschb
 aum\, and Matthew Jackson\, and they have toured and performed in various 
 configurations all over Indiana. Jason was diagnosed with Stage IV Colon C
 ancer in December 2022 and he Dogwoods had their final show in March 2024\
 , which raised nearly $1000 for Man Up to Cancer\, an organization for mal
 es who are fighting or have fought cancer. Jason is the author of three co
 llections of poetry. His most recent through Chatterhouse Press is Battle 
 Scarred. He is also the artist on the spoken word album Revival! Recorded 
 and distributed through Perfect Mix Records. At present\, Jason is complet
 ing several written and recorded projects.\n\n\nTONY BREWER is a poet and 
 audio artist from Bloomington\, Indiana\, where he is executive director o
 f the Spoken Word Stage at the 4th Street Festival of the Arts and Crafts 
 and co-producer of the Writers Guild Spoken Word Series and the Urban Deer
  Performance Series. He has published 12 books and chapbooks\, including m
 ost recently Centaur (with Jonathan S Baker\, Dark Heart Press) and Good J
 ob\, Lightning (Stubborn Mule Press). More at linktr.ee/TonyBrewer\n\nKYLE
  QUASS and JULIAN DOUGLAS have been collaborating for 20 years. Across thi
 s time they have performed in many differing ensembles\, co-led several ba
 nds\, and worked on multiple recording projects. In the process they have 
 formed their own unique shared language blending progressive jazz and cont
 emporary world music. Releases on which they’ve collaborated include Kyle 
 Quass’ Fractured and Julian Douglas’ Talafawa.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20240613T180000
