CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Last Sunday Poetry\nSunday\, July 28\n7:00 PM to 8:30 PM\nMorge
 nstern’s Bookstore & Café\, 849 S Auto Mall Rd\, Bloomington IN 47401\nCol
 umbus OH poets Caidyn Bearfield and Su Flatt\nCAIDYN BEARFIELD (she/her) i
 s a queer Italian-American poet from Columbus\, OH. She has been published
  by River Dog Press and has featured at festivals\, museums\, and punk sho
 ws across the Midwest. She is also a peer and legislative advocate for fos
 ter youth\, who enjoys making anything from crafts to cakes to change.\n\n
 For more about Caidyn: “Caidyn Bearfield finds a way forward through grief
  with *Iniziare* by Andy Downing:\nhttps://matternews.org/…/caidyn-bearfie
 ld-finds-a-way…/\n\nSU FLATT is an Assistant Professor at Columbus State C
 ommunity College\, whose interests are Composition and Rhetoric\, British 
 Literature\, Creative Writing\, and Theory. She is a fierce proponent of t
 he works of women authors\, poets\, and artists\, according to “Q&A: Su Fl
 att of Women Aloud.”\n\nhttps://www.columbusmonthly.com/…/q-su…/2298322800
 7/\n\n“Su Flatt with a love poem” YouTube:\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watc
 h?v=jwmuz6jTwlg\n\n\n\n\n\nEmerging poets who need a supportive audience\,
  and established poets who want to promote published works: Sign up for op
 en mic! Your words are precious. (2-3 min. per open mic participant)\nCome
  early (approx. 30-60 min. before the program start time) to:\n\nSign up f
 or open mic\nMeet and greet program participants\nPurchase food and bevera
 ges before the 7pm cafe closing time\nPurchase copies of books by featured
  poets
