 ' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 325px) 100vw\, 325px' /></a><span style='color
 : #333333\;'>Second Thursday Spoken Word Series</span></p>\n<h2 style='tex
 t-align: left\;'><span style='color: #7e0eed\;'>Staged Reading</span></h2>
 \n<h2 style='text-align: left\;'><span style='color: #7e0eed\;'>a new Merv
 yn Alphonse play</span></h2>\n<h2 style='text-align: left\;'><span style='
 color: #eb0ee7\;'><em>The Deeper You Dig</em></span></h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p> <
 /p>\n<p>A staged reading by Writers Guild members Zilia Balkasky-Sellés\, 
 Joan Hawkins\, Peter Kaczmarczyk\, Shayne Laughter\, Erin Strole\, and Eri
 c Zobel.</p>\n<p><em>An undercover Police officer finds herself in wildly 
 uncharted territory when an assignment takes her back to a traumatic past 
 and to a personal identity that she had hoped to permanently put behind he
 r. Much of the play take place in prison.</em></p>\n<p>Event by Writers Gu
 ild at Bloomington and Tony Brewer</p>\n<p><strong>Free and open to the pu
 blic</strong></p>\n<p>BEER & WINE available for purchase</p>\n<p>THURSDAY\
 , AUG 8<br />\n6pm<br />\nBackspace Gallery\, inside Bonne Fête\, 112 West
  6th Street\, on the square in Bloomington IN</p>\n<p>Sponsored in part by
  the Indiana Arts Commission\, Bloomington Arts Commission\, and the Bloom
 ington Urban Enterprise Association</p>\n<p> </p>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
