DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild at Bloomington presents Last Sunday Poetry\nF
 eaturing Helena Mesa and Doug Paul Case\n \nMorgenstern’s Bookstore & Café
 \, 849 S. Auto Mall Rd.\, Bloomington IN 47401\nSunday\, September 29\, 20
 24\n7-8:30pm\nHELENA MESA is the author of Horse Dance Underwater and a co
 -editor for Mentor & Muse: Essays from Poets to Poets. She teaches at Albi
 on College.\nDOUG PAUL CASE is author of Americanitis\, a book of poems pu
 blished by Ghost City Press in 2023\, and editor of A Flame Called Indiana
 \, an anthology of contemporary Hoosier literature from IU Press. He has p
 ublished five chapbooks of poems since 2015 and currently serves as assist
 ant director of creative writing at Indiana University Bloomington.
