UID:ai1ec-4523@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Join the Writers Guild for an early Halloween celebration!\nFir
 st Sunday Prose Reading Series\nSunday\, October 6\, 2024\n4pm to 5:30pm\n
 Juniper Art Gallery and Cafe\nFeatured Readers will be Rebekah Spivey and 
 James Dorr\, with an open mic to follow.\nPlease no outside food or drink!
 \nPlease note the new start time of 4pm!\n \nRebekah Spivey studied creati
 ve writing and sociology at Indiana University. She has lived and worked o
 n the Isle of Mull in Scotland. She is a lifelong writer and lover of word
 s who has co-created and led a group called Poetry Detectives\, an informa
 l group that discusses poetry in a non-academic way in order to make the g
 enre more approachable. She has a seventeen-year association with Women Wr
 iting for (a) Change\, Bloomington\, a group that supports giving every pe
 rson a voice through writing. Rebekah has been a certified facilitator wit
 h Women Writing since 2013 and currently facilitates a semester-long virtu
 al class. She has coordinated a Women Writing for (a) Change retreat on th
 e Isle of Iona off the west coast of Scotland. And facilitates winter writ
 ing retreats for Women Writing.\nRebekah retired in 2012 from the Indiana 
 Daily Student newspaper at IU after seventeen years as part of the profess
 ional staff.\nShe has been a part-time senior editor for a self-publishing
  company since 2019. And is an editor for private clients.\nRebekah retire
 d in 2012 from the Indiana Daily Student newspaper at IU after seventeen y
 ears as part of the professional staff.\nRebekah’s first novel\, Marigolds
  in Boxes\, was released in September 2024.\n \nA short fiction writer and
  sometime poet\, James Dorr currently harbors a Goth cat named Triana\, an
 d counts among his major influences Ray Bradbury\, Edgar Allan Poe\, Allen
  Ginsberg\, and Bertolt Brecht.  An Indiana resident\, Dorr invites reader
 s to visit his blog at  http://jamesdorrwriter.wordpress.com
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241006T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241006T173000
LOCATION:Juniper Art Gallery and Cafe @ 615 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, 
 IN 7404
SEQUENCE:0
