BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4562@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:A bilingual poetry reading of Marianna Kiyanovska’s work follow
 ed by a conversation with Professor Russell Valentino\, chair of the Slavi
 c and East European Languages and Cultures department\nKiyanovska is one o
 f Ukraine’s most celebrated poets.\nHalina Goldberg\, professor of musicol
 ogy at the IU Jacobs School of Music and director of the IU Byrnes Russian
  and East European Institute\, will introduce the poet. The event will be 
 followed by a small reception.\nThe reading will be bilingual—each poem wi
 ll be read first by the poet in the original Ukrainian\, and each will be 
 followed by a reading of the English translation. See https://books.huri.h
 arvard.edu/authors/336 and https://books.huri.harvard.edu/books/voices-bab
 yn-yar for more information about the poet and her latest book.\n 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241018T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241018T160000
LOCATION:Shreve Auditorium in IU’s Global and International Studies Buildin
 g
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ukraine Poet\, Marianna Kiyanovska\, Conversation and Reading
