X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><p><a href='http
 s://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-mic.jpg'><img
  loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='alignleft' src='https://www.meridi
 ancz.com/de/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/100-post_kyjanowska-e167762
 6821317-810x514.png' alt='Marianna Kiyanovska. War at the end and at the b
 eginning of life |  Internationale Literarische Korporation MERIDIAN CZERN
 OWITZ' width='233' height='148' /></a><span style='color: #000080\;'><stro
 ng>A bilingual poetry reading of Marianna Kiyanovska’s work followed by a 
 conversation with Professor Russell Valentino\, chair of the Slavic and Ea
 st European Languages and Cultures department</strong></span></p>\n<p>Kiya
 novska is one of Ukraine’s most celebrated poets.</p>\n<p>Halina Goldberg\
 , professor of musicology at the IU Jacobs School of Music and director of
  the IU Byrnes Russian and East European Institute\, will introduce the po
 et. The event will be followed by a small reception.</p>\n<p>The reading w
 ill be bilingual—each poem will be read first by the poet in the original 
 Ukrainian\, and each will be followed by a reading of the English translat
 ion. See <a href='https://books.huri.harvard.edu/authors/336'>https://book
 s.huri.harvard.edu/authors/336</a> and <a href='https://books.huri.harvard
 .edu/books/voices-babyn-yar'>https://books.huri.harvard.edu/books/voices-b
 abyn-yar</a> for more information about the poet and her latest book.</p>
 \n<p> </p>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
