BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4544@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents\nThe True Story of the Th
 ree Little Pigs! \non stage October 25 – November 10 at the Waldron Audito
 rium\nA musical “tail” that will bring the house down! There are two sides
  to every story\, and when the Big Bad Wolf takes the stand in Piggsylvani
 a’s Trial of the Century\, he finally gets his say. But whether he’ll get 
 a fair trial in a corrupt piggy court is anyone’s guess. Will the pigs’ sp
 lashy show make a puppet out of justice\, or is the wolf’s song and dance 
 about a sneeze gone wrong all razzle-dazzle? Enter the jury box and help d
 ecide the fate of Big ‘n’ Bad in this musical adaptation of the hit childr
 en’s book.\nFun for all ages! Featuring a Sensory-Friendly performance on 
 Sun\, November 10 at 4:00pm (tickets to this performance are Pay What You 
 Will).\nFor showtimes\, tickets\, and more information\, visit https://see
 constellation.org/kids/three-little-pigs/\n 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241025T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241110T140000
