 e-Pigs-Tile-with-Logo.png 1080w' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 300px) 100vw\, 
 300px' /></a><strong><em><span style='color: #333333\;'>Constellation Stag
 e & Screen presents</span></em></strong></p>\n<h3><strong><span style='col
 or: #ff6600\;'><em>The True Story of the Three Little Pigs!</em> </span></
 strong></h3>\n<p><strong><span style='color: #333333\;'>on stage October 2
 5 – November 10 at the Waldron Auditorium</span></strong></p>\n<p><em>A mu
 sical “tail” that will bring the house down!</em> There are two sides to e
 very story\, and when the Big Bad Wolf takes the stand in Piggsylvania’s T
 rial of the Century\, he finally gets his say. But whether he’ll get a fai
 r trial in a corrupt piggy court is anyone’s guess. Will the pigs’ splashy
  show make a puppet out of justice\, or is the wolf’s song and dance about
  a sneeze gone wrong all razzle-dazzle? Enter the jury box and help decide
  the fate of Big ‘n’ Bad in this musical adaptation of the hit children’s 
 book.</p>\n<p>Fun for all ages! Featuring a <em>Sensory-Friendly performan
 ce</em> on Sun\, November 10 at 4:00pm (tickets to this performance are Pa
 y What You Will).</p>\n<p>For showtimes\, tickets\, and more information\,
  visit <a href='https://seeconstellation.org/kids/three-little-pigs/'>http
 s://seeconstellation.org/kids/three-little-pigs/</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n</BODY
 ></HTML>
