BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4548@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION: \nThe Writers Guild at Bloomington presents \nLast Sunday Poet
 ry\nFeaturing James Dorr and Hysteria\nMorgenstern’s Bookstore & Café\, 84
 9 S. Auto Mall Rd.\, Bloomington IN 47401\nSunday\, October 27\, 2024\n7-8
 :30pm\n \nJAMES DORR‘s Avoid Seeing a Mouse and Other Tales of the Real an
 d Surreal is a January 2024 release from Alien Buddha Press. Other books i
 nclude his 2013 Bram Stoker Award nominee for Fiction Collection\, The Tea
 rs of Isis\, Tombs: A Chronicle of Latter-Day Times of Earth\, and his all
 -poetry Vamps (A Retrospective). Specializing in dark fantasy/horror with 
 forays into mystery and science fiction\, Dorr has been a technical writer
 \, an editor for a regional magazine\, a full-time nonfiction freelancer\,
  and a semi-professional musician. He currently harbors a Goth cat named T
 riana\, and counts among his major influences Ray Bradbury\, Edgar Allan P
 oe\, Allen Ginsberg\, and Bertolt Brecht.\n\nPurchase his books at:\n\n\nh
 ttps://www.amazon.com/stores/author/B004XWCVUS\nHYSTERIA is a poet and per
 formance artist who mixes costume\, theater\, and music into many of her s
 ets. She dances around a few different topics in her writing\, such as tra
 uma\, feminism\, and mental health. Leaning heavily into morbid beauty as 
 well\, her first chapbook\, Nature and the Amygdala (Pure Sleeze Press\, S
 eptember 2024)\, takes you deep into the woods\, straight to the heart of 
 the creatures that dwell there\, and to the part of the brain that holds t
 he fear of the unknown.\n\n\nThis is the Halloween edition of LSP\, so fee
 l free to attend in costume!\n\nEmerging poets who need a supportive audie
 nce\, and established poets who want to promote published works: Sign up f
 or open mic! Your words are precious. (2-3 min. per open mic participant)
 \n\nCome 20-40 min. before the 7pm program start time so you can:\n\n\n– S
 ign up for open mic– Meet and greet featured poets\, and each other– Purch
 ase the store’s books and gift items– Donate to the Writers Guild via cash
 \n\nThe Writers Guild at Bloomington is committed to diversity\, equity\, 
 and inclusivity.\nhttps://writersguildbloomington.com/\n 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241027T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241027T203000
LOCATION:Morgenstern Bookstore & Café @ 849 S. Auto Mall Rd. Bloomington IN
  47401
SEQUENCE:0
