CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Appreciation Event and\nArt Exhibit\n\nfor Writers Guild Member
 \nBronislava Volkova\nVolkova is a Czech-American poet\, scholar\, transla
 tor and artist. She emigrated from Czechoslovakia in 1974 and spent more t
 han 40 years in the United States. She has 22 volumes of poetry in additio
 n to her other work.\nThere will be some music\, and introduction by CAHI 
 director Brenda Weber and Russell Valentino\, and 15-20 minutes of Volkova
  reading her work.\nThis will be followed by a conversation between Volkov
 a\, Eric Rensberger\, and Joan Hawkins about artistic process.\nFriday Nov
 ember 8\, 5-7 p.m. in the College Arts and Humanities Institute on IU Camp
 us–Cook Center for Public Arts and Humanities\, Gayle Karch\, 750 E Kirkwo
 od Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47405 (walk through the Sample Gates and keep go
 ing toward the Indiana Memorial Union).\nThe event will be in the Great Ha
 ll. The event is free and open to the public.
