X-WP-IMAGES-URL:thumbnail\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/u
 ploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1-300x300.png\;300\;300\,medium\;https://
 writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1
 -300x300.png\;300\;300\,large\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-cont
 ent/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1-300x300.png\;300\;300\,full\;https
 ://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarshi
 p-1-300x300.png\;300\;300
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><p><em><a href='
 https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Schol
 arship-1.png'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='alignleft size-m
 edium wp-image-4595' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/u
 ploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1-300x300.png' alt='' width='300' height=
 '300' srcset='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/
 11/Ryser-Scholarship-1-300x300.png 300w\, https://writersguildbloomington.
 com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1-1024x1024.png 1024w\, h
 ttps://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Schola
 rship-1-150x150.png 150w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/
 uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1-768x768.png 768w\, https://writersguil
 dbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1-270x270.pn
 g 270w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Ry
 ser-Scholarship-1-230x230.png 230w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/w
 p-content/uploads/2024/11/Ryser-Scholarship-1.png 1080w' sizes='auto\, (ma
 x-width: 300px) 100vw\, 300px' /></a>The Writers Guild at Bloomington is o
 ffering:</em></p>\n<h3><span style='color: #a30505\;'><strong>The Ryser Sc
 holarship to Writers Guild members to attend a writing workshop or confere
 nce in 2025! </strong></span></h3>\n<p>The scholarship will cover costs up
  to $500.</p>\n<p>Workshops and conferences may cover any literary pursuit
 \, including poetry\, fiction\, non-fiction\, and memoir. Possible in-pers
 on workshops include\, but are not limited to\, the IU Writers Conference 
 in Bloomington\, A Gathering of Writers at Indiana Writers Center\, Indian
 apolis. Virtual workshops such as those offered by Odyssey Writing and out
 -of-state conferences such as those offered by the Highlights Foundation a
 re also eligible.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions\, or to receive an app
 lication form\, please contact Wendy Teller at <a href='mailto:ryseraward@
 writersguildbloomington.com'>ryseraward@writersguildbloomington.com</a></p
 >\n<p><strong>Deadline to apply is December 31\, 2024</strong></p>\n<p><sp
 an style='color: #a30505\;'><em>About the Ryser Scholarship</em></span></p
 >\n<p>The Ryser Scholarship is named for Joan Ryser\, an English teacher w
 ho taught at Bloomington High School South for many years. Before she pass
 ed away\, she instructed her children to direct memorial contributions to 
 a local program to encourage writers. The Writers Guild was honored to be 
 the recipient\, and created an ongoing scholarship to help writers attend 
 a workshop or conference. Each year we offer this award to one of the foll
 owing: an English teacher\, a junior or high school student\, a member of 
 the Writers Guild at Bloomington.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
