BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4578@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Writers Guild at Bloomington Annual Business Meeting\, Potluck\
 , Open Mic and Election!!\n\nDecember 14\, 2024   1-4 pm\n \nFellowship Ro
 om in rear of University Baptist Church (parking in back)   3740 E 3rd St\
 , Bloomington\, IN\nBring a favorite dish to share\, a favorite drink (bee
 r and wine are an option!)\, a poem to read at the open mic\, and  come to
  participate in our annual election\, and vote!! \nNominations are open fo
 r the board positions. You may nominate yourself or someone else. \nThe cu
 rrent Board members: April Ridge\, Hiromi Yoshida and Erin Strole are elig
 ible to run and\nserve again. (The By-Laws stipulate that Board members ma
 y serve up to 5 consecutive\nterms) The only way to vote is to come in per
 son to this meeting!\nBoard position descriptions:\na) The Board of Direct
 ors of the Writers Guild consists of three members elected\nannually. They
  are the Chair\, Secretary\, and Treasurer. Their responsibilities are:\nb
 ) Chair: Calls and presides over board meetings\, business meetings\, memb
 ership\nmeetings\, and elections. Coordinates the committees and calendar 
 for Writers Guild\nproduced events and co-produced events. Leads any fundr
 aising efforts. Has signatory\npower on checks. The Chair may make tempora
 ry appointments for an assistant for\nspecific tasks and projects.\nc) Tre
 asurer: Collects and banks income\, keeps books\, prepares annual financia
 l\nreport\, and submits tax reports. Has signatory power on checks.\nd) Se
 cretary: Keeps minutes of board meetings and makes them available to the\n
 membership. Keeps administrative\, meeting\, and membership records.\ne)  
 Terms & Limits:  Board Members will serve until the end of December of the
  year\nthey were voted into their position. Board members will serve one-y
 ear terms\, and may\nserve five (5) consecutive terms.  Additional terms i
 n the same position may be served\nafter a one-year absence from the Board
  position.\nf)  Board members are required to attend at least sixty percen
 t of all business meetings.\nAny board member who cannot make this commitm
 ent will not be eligible for election\nthe following year.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241214T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20241214T160000
LOCATION:University Baptist Church @ 3740 E 3rd St\, Bloomington\, IN
