 ent Board members: April Ridge\, Hiromi Yoshida and Erin Strole are eligib
 le to run and<br />\nserve again. (The By-Laws stipulate that Board member
 s may serve up to 5 consecutive<br />\nterms) The only way to vote is to c
 ome in person to this meeting!</p>\n<p><em>Board position descriptions:</e
 m></p>\n<p>a) The Board of Directors of the Writers Guild consists of thre
 e members elected<br />\nannually. They are the Chair\, Secretary\, and Tr
 easurer. Their responsibilities are:</p>\n<p>b) <em>Chair:</em> Calls and 
 presides over board meetings\, business meetings\, membership<br />\nmeeti
 ngs\, and elections. Coordinates the committees and calendar for Writers G
 uild<br />\nproduced events and co-produced events. Leads any fundraising 
 efforts. Has signatory<br />\npower on checks. The Chair may make temporar
 y appointments for an assistant for<br />\nspecific tasks and projects.</p
 >\n<p>c) <em>Treasurer:</em> Collects and banks income\, keeps books\, pre
