 ry\n& Open Mic\nfeaturing Doris Lynch and Nancy Chen Long\n\n\n\n\nDORIS J
 EAN LYNCH has recent work in Flying Island\, Modern Haiku\, Acorn\, Stormw
 ash: Environmental Poems\, Wales Haiku Journal\, and Contemporary Haibun O
 nline. Her poems are forthcoming in I-70 Review and Poetry Pea. Lynch’s co
 llection of poems Swimming to Alaska\, which details her year living in an
  Alaskan arctic village\, came out in 2023\, as did Media Hound\, her firs
 t collection of haibun.\nFor an excerpt from Lynch’s *Swimming to Alaska* 
 (Bottom Dog Press\, 18 October 2023)\, visit:\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Swim
 mi…/dp/194750441X/ref=sr_1_3…\nNANCY CHEN LONG is the author of Wider than
  the Sky (Diode Editions\, 2020)\, which was selected for the Diode Editio
 ns Book Award\, and Light into Bodies (University of Tampa Press\, 2017)\,
  winner of the Tampa Review Prize for Poetry. Her poetry has been supporte
 d by a National Endowment of the Arts Creative Writing Fellowship in poetr
 y and the Poetry Society of America Robert H. Winner Award. She works at I
 ndiana University in the Research Technologies division.\nFor an excerpt f
 rom her *Light into Bodies* (University of Tampa Press\, 10 May 2017)\, vi
 sit:\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Light…/dp/1597321478/ref=sr_1_2…\n\n \nSUNDAY
 \, January 26\n7-8:30 PM (EST)\nMorgenstern’s Bookstore & Café\n849 S Auto
  Mall Rd\nBloomington IN 47401
