DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild at Bloomington presents\nA special program ho
 noring Developmental Disability Awareness Month\nFirst Sunday Prose Readin
 g Series \nMarch 2\, 2025 from 4pm to 5:30pm\nJuniper Art Gallery and Cafe
 \nOpen mic to follow\nCome join us!\n \nVirginia Baude\nI was born in Milw
 aukee\, Wisconsin. I have lived in Bloomington\, Indiana the majority of m
 y life. I live with my long-time partner and am the mother to an adult dau
 ghter and pet-mom to a cat and dog. I have been on the Congregational Care
  Committee and am a deacon and send out greeting cards on behalf of our ch
 urch. I started writing some poetry on the inspiration of a friend of mine
  who lives in Texas\, my partner’s father who writes poetry\, and by watch
 ing a Korean drama series called “A Poem a Day.” I like to work on art and
  crafts\, fiber arts\, writing to people\, and playing in our church’s han
 dbell choir.\nCindy Brandes\nI am an artist\, writer\, and crafter. My fav
 orite crafts are knitting\, crocheting\, and watercolor. I love to put my 
 heart into my work\, by thinking of the person that I’m making the project
  for while I work on the project. I love music\, singing and listening to 
 it.
