 849793834_1428762591870264778_n.jpg 480w' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 186px)
  100vw\, 186px' /></a></p>\n<p>🎨<strong><span style='color: #800080\;'>PDV
 NCH</span></strong>👌🏾 [pee-dove-inch]<br />\nis a spoken wordsmith and dra
 matic prophetic poetic storyteller\, who uses rainbows\, painting pictures
 \, creating vivid images\, with words\, from multiple perspectives\, givin
 g voice to the unheard\, with vocal tones\, that are rhythmic.</p>\n<p sty
 le='padding-left: 40px\;'>As an inventor/originator\, most known\, globall
 y\, for his original iconic hair designs ‘Beads by DVNCH’\, fabulous frame
 s and his phenomenal passion for fashion.</p>\n<p style='padding-left: 200
 px\;'>A Bloomingtonian\, and Director Of Creative-Arts Productions for !ℵṧ
 ℘!Իḙ-!ℵṧ℘!Իᾰт!✺ℵ-!ℵ!т!ᾰт!ṽḙ @ !3 studios. Through collaboration\, his desi
 re is to Inspire inspiration\, and “Always be on Purpose”!</p>\n<p><span s
 tyle='color: #0000ff\;'>First Sunday Prose Reading – <strong>Open Mic to f
 ollow!</strong></span></p>\n<p>Sunday\, May 4\, 2025</p>\n<p>The Juniper A
 rt Gallery and Cafe</p>\n<p><a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/61
 5+W\,+Kirkwood+Avenue?entry=gmail&source=g' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
  data-saferedirecturl='https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.google.com
 /maps/search/615%2BW\,%2BKirkwood%2BAvenue?entry%3Dgmail%26source%3Dg&sour
 ce=gmail&ust=1731017030177000&usg=AOvVaw1VWs9ce8feFaTPQlKHN82O'>615 W. Kir
 kwood Avenue</a></p>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4732@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:Writers Guild Spoken Word Series\n\n \nPoets Michael Duckwall\n
 Patty Cooper Wells\nMusic by Tommy Bays\n\nOpen mic to follow\nSponsored i
 n part by the Bloomington Arts Commission and the Bloomington Urban Enterp
 rise Association\nMICHAEL DUCKWALL was born and raised in the Ohio Valley.
  A featured poet at the 10th Gonzofest in 2023\, he took off and hit the g
 round running as part of the production team for a 57-hour non-stop “Insom
 niacathon” music and poetry event in Louisville KY in 2024. Michael’s poet
 ry\, artwork\, and photography have been in a handful of magazines and ant
 hologies\, along with numerous online features. He has a couple of chapboo
 ks—“Ramblings of a Recovering Poet” and “7.2 SkullQuake”—in publication an
 d one limited-edition co-authored chapbook\, “Kraken Nuts” (w/ Chad M. Hor
 n)\, you may have missed out on.\n\nPATTY COOPER WELLS is a native of Quee
 nsville IN. She and her husband\, John\, have made Madison their home sinc
 e 2000. Primarily a visual artist\, she believes art is calling and revels
  in the creative process. She studied art with Cal-Arts alumni artist Paul
  E. Neufelder at his Magic Theatre Studio in Columbus IN. She has painted 
 and exhibited her artwork for over thirty-five years. She has painted many
  murals all over Madison: The Taproom\, Analog Coffee\, and River of Kindn
 ess at Mural Plaza are three of the best known. Her other passions are loc
 al history\, genealogy\, and vintage Halloween. She is a volunteer curator
  at Gallery @ the SPOT/M.A.A.A.\, and co-founder of The Gadfly Art & Poeti
 cs Society with Jane Vonderheide.\nTOMMY BAYS is an eclectic singer/songwr
 iter and multi-instrumentalist with a passion for the written word and lon
 g funky grooves. He hails from the Louisville KY and southern Indiana area
  and is a member of US Lifetime National Beat Poet Laureate Ron Whitehead’
 s Storm Generation Band. Tommy has been performing music with poets for ma
 ny years\, including at events produced by Keeping the Flame Alive. He is 
 working his debut solo album and wants you to know before he performs thes
 e 3 things: you can feel good\, we want you to be happy\, and you can stil
 l have fun. Surrender to the flow. Catch Tommy at this year’s GonzoFest Ne
 w Orleans in May!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20250508T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20250508T200000
LOCATION:Backspace Gallery @ 112 W 6th St on the square in Bloomington IN
SEQUENCE:0
