BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4730@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild at Bloomington presents\nThe launch reading o
 f Hiromi Yoshida’s 5th poetry chapbook Umami (Alien Buddha Press\, 26 Marc
 h 2025)\n\n \n \n“Hiromi Yoshida offers up a delectable assortment of poem
 s with Umami. Taste is the thing and getting at the intangible yet discern
 able vibe of these dishes is what’s on the menu. Lighter fare than Yoshida
  is typically known for\, these poems entice with clear observant details 
 and careful surveys of the palate. Here we are treated to dishes both trad
 itional and modern\, ethnic and monocultural. Childhood memories conjure u
 p TV dinners in America or sticky hands in Taipei. And of course\, Icarus 
 remains\, reduced by now to name-dropped specter. Salad fork\, not centerp
 iece. A distant speck: “floating signifier like that solitary / cheese tha
 t couldn’t stand / alone\, grilled for his stupidity.” Hiromi Yoshida’s Um
 ami is a feast for the poetic senses.”\n—Tony Brewer\, 2024 Indiana Litera
 ry Champion\nAlso Featured:\nAPRIL RIDGE lurks in the rural hilltops of Mo
 nroe County\, akin to Mothman’s tomboy cousin\, listening for hints of poe
 try on the wind. She enjoys horror films\, the sordid affairs of 1920s cir
 cus performers\, long walks in pitch black tunnels and the occasional waff
 le cone from Jiffy Treet. She prides herself on finding the perfect outfit
  in which to adorn the skeleton of the soul. She hopes to highlight the ne
 eds of poems in danger\, on the run\, escaping from the need to fit into o
 ne form or another\, on their way to the freedom of epiphany.\n\nApril ser
 ves as chair of the Writers Guild at Bloomington\, and is a nominee for Be
 st of the Net and the Pushcart Prize. Her debut poetry chapbook is Monstro
 us (Pure Sleeze Press\, 2024) and her forthcoming first full-length collec
 tion is A Three Night Affair (Keeping The Flame Alive Press\, fall 2025).
 \n\nJoin us for an umami-filled evening of poetry and food!\nOpen mic to f
 ollow readings.\n5.16.25 (6-8 PM)\nRuncible Spoon Restaurant & Café\, 412 
 E 6th St\, Bloomington\, IN 47408
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20250516T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20250516T200000
LOCATION:Runcible Spoon Restaurant & Café @ 412 E 6th St\, Bloomington\, IN
  47408
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Umami Book Launch Reading & Open Mic
URL:https://writersguildbloomington.com/event/umami-book-launch-reading-ope
 n-mic/
X-COST-TYPE:free
