 \n<h4 style='text-align: right\;'></h4>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>f
 eaturing author and audio playwright <span style='color: #0000ff\;'>Brian 
 Price</span><br class='html-br' />with musical accompaniment by <span styl
 e='color: #0000ff\;'>Kyle Quass & Julian Douglas</span><br class='html-br'
  />performing <span style='color: #0000ff\;'>THE LAST COYOTE</span></p>\n<
 p style='text-align: center\;'><span style='color: #0000ff\;'><strong>Open
  mic to follow</strong></span></p>\n<p style='text-align: center\;'>Sponso
 red in part by the Bloomington Arts Commission and the Bloomington Urban E
 nterprise Association</p>\n<div class='x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs x
 tlvy1s' style='text-align: center\;'></div>\n<div class='x11i5rnm xat24cr 
 x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'><strong><span style='color: #0000ff\;'>BRIAN PRI
 CE</span></strong> is a writer\, director\, and audio producer. He has wor
 ked in radio and audio publishing since the 1980s working with groups such
  as the Iowa Radio Project\, The Grist Mill Horror Series\, Native Voices 
 at the Autry\, and the National Audio Theatre Festivals. His short comic s
 kits\, plays\, and monologues have been performed by community groups acro
 ss the country and two of his plays have been translated into Croatian and
  Chinese. He is a founding partner in Great Northern Audio Theatre which c
 reated and produced 20 years of live Mark Time Radio shows for Minnesota’s
  Convergence Science Fiction Convention. Their feature-length “In the Embe
 rs” received an APA Audie Award for Best Audio Drama in 2017. He has publi
 shed two books of short fiction\, monologues and poetry\, “The Old Cart Wr
 angler\, The New Silence\, and Other Notions” (2020)\, and “The Wrong Side
  of the River and Other Points of Interest” (2022)\, He has some concerns 
 about the general future of mankind\, and often gets paid in T-shirts and 
 “gimme hats.” He is a member in good standing of the “The Electroacoustica
 l Poetical Society.” <a class='x1i10hfl xjbqb8w x1ejq31n xd10rxx x1sy0etr 
 x17r0tee x972fbf xcfux6l x1qhh985 xm0m39n x9f619 x1ypdohk xt0psk2 xe8uvvx 
 xdj266r x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r xexx8yu x4uap5 x18d9i69 xkhd6sd x16tdsg8
  x1hl2dhg xggy1nq x1a2a7pz xkrqix3 x1sur9pj x1fey0fg x1s688f' tabindex='0'
  role='link' href='https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greatno
 rthernaudio.com%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExQzU1Tkl5N1I3eU5MRE
 h5ZAEezvjr6NbIP3YJ-i2o__ztzqIXebEKxH51-z7N0heWhjws_hrIrbTI4rfPYdM_aem_lDMr
 CqEtRfmK2yB6lnbbDg&h=AT1BzMULABl3R3sIw8I2lj4O-pSbH37mF4gz3mmYtHhzFkKYPZfrU
 WET2Cu7f5FMK-iTrygb1EfjWM_FadnkrYDToZOIJZA--5m1BsABgbLA7M8z8_83CzUOlkt92yz
 f9UUgb_Nohi9u0Q&__tn__=q&c[0]=AT1NSigjzNQSD3R1JcxEIgbc0ywB7uysp2DLtEB2eb9n
 5YYTt_vCBUrtrnVFjnLb-4zf5LV1GX3PsD6-JoUIsmNuOpcs0NkTSOPKyUe93cLEDtJCYpzkRV
 bx1s8u3E55kpznhmdCq25NjQACSIvoKoulD9Ug0ExlFyNrRg' target='_blank' rel='nof
 ollow noopener noreferrer'>www.greatnorthernaudio.com</a></p>\n</div>\n<di
 v></div>\n<div class='x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'><strong><
 span style='color: #0000ff\;'>KYLE QUASS</span></strong> and <strong><span
  style='color: #0000ff\;'>JULIAN DOUGLAS</span></strong> have been collabo
 rating for 20 years. Across this time they have performed in many differin
 g ensembles\, co-led several bands\, and worked on multiple recording proj
 ects. In the process they have formed their own unique shared language ble
 nding progressive jazz and contemporary world music. Releases on which the
 y’ve collaborated include Kyle Quass’ Fractured and Julian Douglas’ Talafa
 wa.</div>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
