DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild at Bloomington presents \nLast Sunday Poetry 
 & Open Mic\nfeaturing Zach Hannah and Su Flatt\n\n\n \nZACH HANNAH is an A
 ppalachian expat originally from Portsmouth\, OH\, now residing in Columbu
 s\, OH. A poet\, an instigator of poetry\, and one half of the SandWich Ar
 ts duo\, alongside Su Flatt\, Zach has taken notes from the creativity and
  vision of the now retired Writers’ Block Open Mic\, producing and co-prod
 ucing several public events centered around poetry\, including the now ann
 ual megaphone reading\, SHHH\, They’ll Hear You\, and 6-1-FORT\, A Poetic 
 Excuse (to build poetry forts\, of course.) He is also the 2nd resident fo
 r the Johnstone’s Fund For New Music.\nSU FLATT bio forthcoming.\n\n\nEmer
 ging poets who need a supportive audience\, and established poets who want
  to promote published works: Come 20-50 min. before the 7pm program start 
 time so you can sign up for open mic! Your words are precious. (2-3 min. p
 er open mic participant)\n7-8:30 PM (EST) 29 June 2025\nMorgenstern Books 
 & Cafe (849 S Auto Mall Rd\, Bloomington IN 47401)
