X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><p><strong><em>T
 he Writers Guild at Bloomington presents </em><span style='color: #3366ff\
 ;'>Last Sunday Poetry & Open Mic</span></strong></p>\n<h3><span style='col
 or: #3366ff\;'><strong>featuring JL Kato and John K. Kruschke</strong></sp
 an></h3>\n<p class='x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'><a href='ht
 tps://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/515436199_113
 2694378883184_7135622333830226317_n.jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='asy
 nc' class='alignleft wp-image-4891 size-medium' src='https://writersguildb
 loomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/515436199_1132694378883184_71356
 22333830226317_n-300x173.jpg' alt='' width='300' height='173' srcset='http
 s://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/515436199_11326
 94378883184_7135622333830226317_n-300x173.jpg 300w\, https://writersguildb
 loomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/515436199_1132694378883184_71356
 22333830226317_n-1024x590.jpg 1024w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/
 wp-content/uploads/2025/04/515436199_1132694378883184_7135622333830226317_
 n-768x442.jpg 768w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/upload
 s/2025/04/515436199_1132694378883184_7135622333830226317_n-1536x884.jpg 15
 36w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/51543
 6199_1132694378883184_7135622333830226317_n.jpg 2048w' sizes='auto\, (max-
 width: 300px) 100vw\, 300px' /></a></p>\n<p class='x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g
 0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'><strong><span style='color: #3366ff\;'>JL Kato’s </spa
 n></strong>poetry collection\, Shadows Set in Concrete (Restoration Press\
 , 2010)\, was selected as a Best Book of Indiana in 2011. A longtime ambas
 sador of the literary arts\, he was chosen as 2022 Literary Champion by th
 e Indiana Authors Awards.</p>\n<div class='x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkb
 s xtlvy1s'>\n<p>JL was born in Japan\, and moved to Indiana at age two. He
  graduated from Indiana University with a degree in journalism\, and worke
 d as a newspaper copy editor for 31 years.</p>\n</div>\n<div class='x14z9m
 p xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'>Former president of Etheridge Knight I
 nc. and Brick Street Poetry (organizations that sponsor literary events\, 
 readings\, contests\, and publications)\, JL was also a co-founder and cur
 ator of Poetry in Free Motion\, a collaborative project between poets and 
 quilters.</div>\n<div class='x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'>JL 
 moderated the Poetry Salon for the Indiana Writers Center\, encouraging po
 ets to develop their writing and critiquing skills. He also served for six
  years as poetry editor of Flying Island Journal\, and now volunteers as a
  judge for the annual writing contest for incarcerated persons\, sponsored
  by the Woman’s Press Club of Indiana.</div>\n<p class='x11i5rnm xat24cr x
 1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'><strong><span style='color: #3366ff\;'><br />\n</
 span></strong><span style='color: #3366ff\;'><strong>JOHN K. KRUSCHKE’s </
 strong></span>poems have been published in a variety of journals including
  Blue Unicorn\, Stickman Review\, The Tipton Poetry Journal\, Sage Magazin
 e\, The Lake\, and Flying Island Literary Journal. He has also published n
 umerous articles in scientific journals on topics ranging across moral psy
 chology\, learning theory\, and Bayesian statistics. He is Provost Profess
 or Emeritus of Psychological and Brain Sciences at Indiana University\, Bl
 oomington.</p>\n<p>Emerging poets who need a supportive audience\, and est
 ablished poets who want to promote published works: Come 20-50 min. before
  the 7pm program start time so you can sign up for open mic! Your words ar
 e precious. (2-3 min. per open mic participant)</p>\n<div class='x11i5rnm 
 xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'>\n<p>7-8:30 PM (EST)<br />\nMorgenstern 
 Books & Cafe (849 S Auto Mall Rd\, Bloomington IN 47401)</p>\n</div>\n</BO
 DY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-4959@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION: \n\nConstellation Stage & Screen presents the Tony and Pulitze
 r Prize-Winning Rock Musical Next to Normal\, on stage September 4-21 at t
 he Waldron Auditorium in downtown Bloomington.\n\n\nExperience the electri
 fying rock musical that delves into the heart of a family shattered by men
 tal illness but held together by love. Diana Goodman\, a suburban mom batt
 ling bipolar disorder\, struggles to connect with her ambitious daughter a
 nd devoted husband as they navigate the chaos of Diana’s condition. With a
  soaring\, unforgettable score by Tom Kitt and poignant book and lyrics by
  Brian Yorkey\, Next to Normal is an unflinching\, empathetic portrait of 
 resilience\, loss\, and the pursuit of hope. Hailed by The New York Times 
 as a “transformative\,” “feel-everything” musical\, this modern masterpiec
 e is a must-see theatrical event.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFor showtimes\, tickets\,
  and more information\, visit https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/next-
 to-normal/\n\n\n\n\nTickets: https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/next-t
 o-normal/.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20250904T193000
LOCATION:The John & Linda Whikehart Auditorium | Waldron Arts Center @ 122 
 S Walnut St\, Bloomington
