DESCRIPTION:Join the Writers Guild for the First Sunday Prose Reading:\nWri
 ters Gabriel Peoples and Jake Williger\n\nGabriel Peoples is an associate 
 professor of Gender Studies whose research is located at the nexus of perf
 ormance\, gender\, and Africana studies. In Goin’ Viral: Uncontrollable Bl
 ack Performance\, he explores how Black people and their representations g
 o viral and what happens when they do from the 18th-century to present.\n 
 \n \n \n\nJ. M. Williger is an author originally from Porter\, Indiana\, w
 ho made his literary debut last year with The Rites of Iron\, the first no
 vel in The Trials of Gnash series. He currently lives in Indianapolis with
  his partner Maya and their dog Bloo.\n \n \n \nFirst Sunday Prose Reading
  – Open Mic to follow!\nSunday\, September 7\, 2025\nThe Juniper Art Galle
 ry and Cafe 615 W. Kirkwood Avenue
