DESCRIPTION: \n\nConstellation Stage & Screen presents the Tony and Pulitze
 r Prize-Winning Rock Musical Next to Normal\, on stage September 4-21 at t
 he Waldron Auditorium in downtown Bloomington.\n\n\nExperience the electri
 fying rock musical that delves into the heart of a family shattered by men
 tal illness but held together by love. Diana Goodman\, a suburban mom batt
 ling bipolar disorder\, struggles to connect with her ambitious daughter a
 nd devoted husband as they navigate the chaos of Diana’s condition. With a
  soaring\, unforgettable score by Tom Kitt and poignant book and lyrics by
  Brian Yorkey\, Next to Normal is an unflinching\, empathetic portrait of 
 resilience\, loss\, and the pursuit of hope. Hailed by The New York Times 
 as a “transformative\,” “feel-everything” musical\, this modern masterpiec
 e is a must-see theatrical event.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFor showtimes\, tickets\,
  and more information\, visit https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/next-
 to-normal/\n\n\n\n\nTickets: https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/next-t
 o-normal/.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20250921T140000
LOCATION:The John & Linda Whikehart Auditorium | Waldron Arts Center @ 122 
 S Walnut St\, Bloomington
SEQUENCE:0
