DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild at Bloomington presents Last Sunday Poetry & 
 Open Mic\n\nfeaturing Peter Kaczmarczyk and Bruce Kell\nOpen mic to follow
 \n\nPETER KACZMARCZYK was raised in New England and has lived the last 30 
 years in Southern Indiana. Most of his works strive to tell short tales in
  simple words that are accessible to all. Author of three poetry chapbooks
 \, his poems have also been published in numerous journals and several ant
 hologies. He is co-creator of the Captain Janeway Statue in Bloomington\, 
 Indiana.\nBRUCE KELL is a long-time resident of Bloomington and a graduate
  of Indiana University. In addition to writing\, he paints\, draws\, cooks
 \, sings and plays guitar and flute. He and his wife\, Ann\, love to trave
 l and call San Miguel de Allende in Mexico their second home.\n\n \n\n\n7-
 8:30 PM (EST)\nMorgenstern Books & Cafe (849 S Auto Mall Rd\, Bloomington 
 IN 47401)
