BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ai1ec-5015@writersguildbloomington.com
DTSTAMP:20260309T020724Z
CATEGORIES:
CONTACT:
DESCRIPTION:The Writers Guild at Bloomington presents Last Sunday Poetry & 
 Open Mic\n\nfeaturing James Dorr and April Ridge\nOpen mic to follow\n\n\n
  \n\n\n\nJAMES DORR’s Avoid Seeing a Mouse and Other Tales of the Real and
  Surreal is a January 2024 release from Alien Buddha Press. Other books in
 clude his 2013 Bram Stoker Award® nominee for Fiction Collection\, The Tea
 rs of Isis\, Tombs: A Chronicle of Latter-Day Times of Earth\, and his all
 -poetry Vamps (A Retrospective). Specializing in dark fantasy/horror with 
 forays into mystery and science fiction\, Dorr has been a technical writer
 \, an editor on a regional magazine\, a full-time nonfiction freelancer\, 
 and a semi-professional musician. He currently harbors a Goth cat named Tr
 iana\, and counts among his major influences Ray Bradbury\, Edgar Allan Po
 e\, Allen Ginsberg\, and Bertolt Brecht.\nAPRIL RIDGE lurks in the rural h
 illtops of Monroe County\, akin to Mothman’s tomboy cousin\, listening for
  hints of poetry on the wind. She enjoys horror films\, the sordid affairs
  of 1920s circus performers\, long walks in pitch black tunnels and the oc
 casional waffle cone from Jiffy Treet. April prides herself on finding the
  perfect outfit in which to adorn the skeleton of the soul. She hopes to h
 ighlight the needs of poems in danger\, on the run\, escaping from the nee
 d to fit into one form or another\, on their way to the freedom of epiphan
 y. Her work has appeared sporadically in deep space\, circling black holes
  until the dinner bell of eternal fame rings in its echoing chambers.\nEme
 rging poets who need a supportive audience\, and established poets who wan
 t to promote published works: Sign up for open mic! Your words are preciou
 s. The time limit per open mic participant is 3-5 min. depending on the nu
 mber signed up (e.g. 3.75 min. if 12).\nArrive 20-50 min. before the 7pm p
 rogram start time so you can:\n– Sign up for open mic\n– Meet and greet fe
 atured poets\, and each other\n– Purchase the store’s books and other gift
  items\n– Order and enjoy cafe food and beverages\nMore information about 
 the Writers Guild at Bloomington:\nhttps://writersguildbloomington.com/\nT
 he Writers Guild at Bloomington is committed to fostering diversity\, and 
 welcomes members regardless of gender\, race\, sexual orientation\, religi
 ous affiliation\, and ability.\n7-8:30 PM (EST)\nMorgenstern Books & Cafe 
 (849 S Auto Mall Rd\, Bloomington IN 47401)
