 /08/546214790_1189801246505830_8181105135888652863_n-300x189.jpg\;300\;189
 \,full\;https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/546
 214790_1189801246505830_8181105135888652863_n-300x189.jpg\;300\;189
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC '-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//E
 N'>\\n<HTML>\\n<HEAD>\\n<TITLE></TITLE>\\n</HEAD>\\n<BODY><p><strong><em>T
 he Writers Guild at Bloomington presents </em><span style='color: #3366ff\
 ;'>Last Sunday Poetry & Open Mic</span></strong></p>\n<p class='x11i5rnm x
 at24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'><a href='https://writersguildbloomington.
 com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/546214790_1189801246505830_8181105135888652
 863_n.jpg'><img loading='lazy' decoding='async' class='wp-image-5024 size-
 medium alignleft' src='https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uplo
 ads/2025/08/546214790_1189801246505830_8181105135888652863_n-300x189.jpg' 
 alt='' width='300' height='189' srcset='https://writersguildbloomington.co
 m/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/546214790_1189801246505830_818110513588865286
 3_n-300x189.jpg 300w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uplo
 ads/2025/08/546214790_1189801246505830_8181105135888652863_n-1024x644.jpg 
 1024w\, https://writersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/546
 214790_1189801246505830_8181105135888652863_n-768x483.jpg 768w\, https://w
 ritersguildbloomington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/546214790_1189801246
 505830_8181105135888652863_n-1536x966.jpg 1536w\, https://writersguildbloo
 mington.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/546214790_1189801246505830_81811051
 35888652863_n.jpg 2048w' sizes='auto\, (max-width: 300px) 100vw\, 300px' /
 ></a></p>\n<h3 style='font-weight: 400\;'><span style='color: #3366ff\;'><
 strong>featuring James Dorr and April Ridge</strong></span></h3>\n<p style
 ='font-weight: 400\;'><strong>Open mic to follow</strong></p>\n<hr />\n<di
 v class='x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'>\n<p> </p>\n</div>\n<di
 v class='x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s'>\n<p><span style='colo
 r: #0000ff\;'><br />\n<strong>JAMES DORR</strong></span>’s Avoid Seeing a 
 Mouse and Other Tales of the Real and Surreal is a January 2024 release fr
 om Alien Buddha Press. Other books include his 2013 Bram Stoker Award® nom
 inee for Fiction Collection\, The Tears of Isis\, Tombs: A Chronicle of La
 tter-Day Times of Earth\, and his all-poetry Vamps (A Retrospective). Spec
 ializing in dark fantasy/horror with forays into mystery and science ficti
 on\, Dorr has been a technical writer\, an editor on a regional magazine\,
  a full-time nonfiction freelancer\, and a semi-professional musician. He 
 currently harbors a Goth cat named Triana\, and counts among his major inf
 luences Ray Bradbury\, Edgar Allan Poe\, Allen Ginsberg\, and Bertolt Brec
 ht.</p>\n<p><span style='color: #0000ff\;'><strong>APRIL RIDGE</strong></s
 pan> lurks in the rural hilltops of Monroe County\, akin to Mothman’s tomb
 oy cousin\, listening for hints of poetry on the wind. She enjoys horror f
 ilms\, the sordid affairs of 1920s circus performers\, long walks in pitch
  black tunnels and the occasional waffle cone from Jiffy Treet. April prid
 es herself on finding the perfect outfit in which to adorn the skeleton of
  the soul. She hopes to highlight the needs of poems in danger\, on the ru
 n\, escaping from the need to fit into one form or another\, on their way 
 to the freedom of epiphany. Her work has appeared sporadically in deep spa
 ce\, circling black holes until the dinner bell of eternal fame rings in i
 ts echoing chambers.</p>\n<p>Emerging poets who need a supportive audience
 \, and established poets who want to promote published works: Sign up for 
 open mic! Your words are precious. The time limit per open mic participant
  is 3-5 min. depending on the number signed up (e.g. 3.75 min. if 12).</p>
 \n<p>Arrive 20-50 min. before the 7pm program start time so you can:<br />
 \n– Sign up for open mic<br />\n– Meet and greet featured poets\, and each
  other<br />\n– Purchase the store’s books and other gift items<br />\n– O
 rder and enjoy cafe food and beverages</p>\n<p>More information about the 
 Writers Guild at Bloomington:<br />\n<a href='https://writersguildblooming
 ton.com/'>https://writersguildbloomington.com/</a></p>\n<p>The Writers Gui
 ld at Bloomington is committed to fostering diversity\, and welcomes membe
 rs regardless of gender\, race\, sexual orientation\, religious affiliatio
 n\, and ability.</p>\n<p>7-8:30 PM (EST)<br />\nMorgenstern Books & Cafe (
 849 S Auto Mall Rd\, Bloomington IN 47401)</p>\n</div>\n</BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
